title: chicken-n-rice casserole
directions: Layer pan with rice; top with chopped chicken.
Mix soup, broth and onion.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until piping hot.

title: minestrone
directions: Brown meat in olive oil with spices.
Add broth, water, bouillon and Italian dressing.
Cover and cook 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Add it the last 30 minutes of cooking.
Serve with hot French bread slices.
Enjoy!

title: bachelor's mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Put in a bowl, making a hole, with potatoes on all sides.
Melt 1 stick of butter and pour into hole.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces (this takes about 2 months).
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for about 4 weeks at 465°.
Will serve 380 people. If more are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added.
Do this only if necessary; most people do not like hair in their stew.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Layer refried beans on serving plate.
Mash avocados with beater and add lemon juice.
Layer on top of refried beans. Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning mix.
Layer on top avocado mixture, then green onions, tomatoes and black olives.
Top with cheese.
Assemble and refrigerate 1 hour before serving with corn chips.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine almonds, water and food coloring; let stand.
Combine gelatin, milk, coconut and nuts.
Mix well; shape candies to look like strawberries.
Dip top of candy in green sugar crystals (or use tube icing).
Roll bottom in red sugar crystals.
Insert green slivered almond in top to form stem.

title: cheesecake
directions: In large bowl, cream the cheese, one package at a time. Gradually add flour and blend well.
Add sugar a little at a time and blend until smooth.
Beat in lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat in eggs and egg yolks one at a time until fluffy.
Pour into a spring-form pan in which the bottom has been covered with graham cracker crust.
Bake at 500° for 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to 200° and continue baking for 40 to 50 minutes.
When done, run knife around outside of pan before removing.
Pie is done when top begins to crack and turn golden brown.
Toothpick should come out clean.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt, pepper, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Boil noodles.
Mix with hamburger mixture.
Pour in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1/4 hour at 350°.

title: atlanta gas light hot olive puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Stir in flour and cayenne pepper, mixing well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of dough around each olive, completely covering olive.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 24.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Dip chicken in butter.
Coat with the combined dry ingredients.
Place in pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: hot and spicy peanuts
directions: Heat oil in 8-inch skillet over medium heat.
Cook garlic in oil, stirring occasionally, until garlic is golden brown.
Remove garlic and discard.
Stir peanuts and chili powder into skillet. Cook over medium heat about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally, until peanuts are warm.
Drain.
Sprinkle with salt and cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container at room temperature.

title: butter cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add flour and vanilla. Dough should be soft, but not stiff (should be able to hold in your hand without it sticking).
If too stiff, add a tablespoon of milk. Make balls about the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with fingers or bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, water, oil and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate candy balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together with hands and/or wooden spoon. Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Melt the molding chocolate in top of a double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate. Remove with tongs.
Place on wax paper to set. (Can be put into refrigerator to set.)
Makes 100 to 150 balls.

title: fluffy salmon cakes
directions: Add to salmon juice 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder.
Mix into rest of ingredients and form into small patties.
Fry in hot Crisco for about 5 minutes until brown.
Serve with tartar sauce or Caesar dressing.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Cream together the ingredients and spread over jello. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Lightly brown beef in Wesson oil in skillet.
Add onion and celery (or pepper) and brown.
Remove excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and let simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese before serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except almonds) and press down onto bottom of a large spring-form pan.
Sprinkle sliced almonds on top of crust.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in black skillet or heavy pan.
Stir in milk and eggs, pinch of salt.
Let cook until thick, stir if needed.
Add 2 Tbsp. butter, 1 tsp vanilla.
Pour in baked crust. Top with cool whip or beat the egg whites and use for meringue.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer the ingredients on a large dinner plate as listed. Keep in fridge.
Serve with nacho chips,

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Dump pineapple in a 9 x 13 inch pan and spread evenly, dump the cherries on top and spread without mixing the pineapple.
Dump the cake mix into pan and spread evenly without mixing the other ingredients.
Cut butter into pats and cover the top of the cake.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding, orange juice and milk.
Add the sour cream.
Pour over the fruit.

title: slow cooker chicken cacciatore(five to seven hours cooking time)
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Arrange onion rings in bottom of slow cooker.
Top with chicken.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Shape into balls.
Put in skillet and pour remaining 2 cups tomato sauce over meatballs.
Bring to boil.
Reduce and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry-peach sauce
directions: Place strawberries in container of an electric blender or food processor; process until smooth.
Pour through wire-mesh strainer; press strawberries with back of a spoon against the sides of the strainer to squeeze out juice.
Discard seeds.
Combine strawberry juice, peach nectar, and next 2 ingredients in a saucepan.
Add peaches; cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve warm or at room temperature with pound cake. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend together butter and Crisco; add sugar blend well.
Add 5 eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and salt together.
Alternate flour and milk; add vanilla extract.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake 325° 1 hour and 35 minutes.
This is an old family recipe.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add milk to make 1 gallon.

title: dill pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers; pack loosely in hot quart jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace. For each quart, add dill and mustard seed. Make a brine by combining water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to boiling. Slowly pour hot brine over cucumbers, leaving 1/2 inch headspace. Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes. (Start timing as soon as jars are placed in water.)

title: candy yams
directions: Cover bottom of pan with sugar, cinnamon and pats of butter. Add large slices of uncooked sweet potatoes until area is covered. Sprinkle sweet potatoes with 1/2 tablespoon of lemon peel.
Add sliced oranges with peeling on top.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole.
Pour water over it. Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour and, uncovered, for 1/2 hour. (Total baking time is 1 1/2 hours.)
Serves 6.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 420°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in blueberries and water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; boil and stir for 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir remaining ingredients until soft dough forms.
Drop dough, dividing in 6 tablespoon size, onto hot blueberry mix.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Serve with cream if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas tree bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Let stand a few minutes, then stir until dissolved.
Add salt, sugar, cooled milk, butter, eggs and 4 cups flour.
Beat with spoon until well mixed.
Stir in remaining flour and rest of ingredients and mix well.
Turn out on a slightly floured board.
Add flour as needed to prevent sticking. Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until double in size.
This takes about 2 1/2 hours.

title: apple pastry
directions: Cook apples as directed.
Add ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon. (You can omit any of these if it is not desired.)
Stir constantly.
Thaw pastry sheets according to directions on package.
Cut pastry sheets in any shape.
The more you make these the better you can work with it.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of apple mixture into each piece of pastry.
Twist or fold to cover apple mixture.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 350° to 400° until brown. Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.
Great for the holidays!

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet.
Pour off grease. Stir in all the remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: butterscotch cream cheese bars
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butterscotch chips and butter over low heat.
Stir in cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Reserve 2/3 of mixture.
Press remainder firmly into bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch ovenproof glass baking dish, making uniform layers. Heat oven to 325°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into ball.
Roll in nuts and chill.

title: easy no name dessert
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until well chilled.
Can be put in graham cracker pie crust.

title: red raspberry jelly(yields 3 to 4 pints)
directions: In a heavy saucepan, add measured juice, 1 pouch Certo fruit pectin or 2 pouches for additional firmness and 1 pad of margarine or butter.
Bring to a boil and add measured sugar.
When it reaches a rolling boil that cannot be stirred down, continue by constantly stirring for 2 minutes.
Turn heat off and immediately skim foam, then seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: chili sauce
directions: I add some sweet red pepper if I have it.
Gives a nice color. Boil until thick in a heavy saucepan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Top with topping mixture and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate lovers cake
directions: Mix together bake in 9 x 13 or bunt pan at 350 for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for five minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Stir peanut butter until melted.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and mix well with other ingredients.
Let stand overnight before using.

title: 3 day eclair cake
directions: Fold Cool Whip into pudding mix. One layer crackers, one layer pudding, Cool Whip mix, another layer crackers, rest of pudding, Cool Whip mix, layer of crackers, frosting.
Refrigerate for 3 days.

title: three cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, 1/4 cup picante sauce, diced pepper, onion and cumin.
Mix well.

title: western potato salad
directions: In large
salad
bowl,	thoroughly combine all ingredients, except potatoes.
Toss
with
warm	potatoes.
Cover and chill. Makes about 10 side dish servings.	(Dry dill weed may be used.)

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt oleo in large bowl; add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add sugar and crumbs.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread very thin layer over crust mix.
Refrigerate only until chocolate is set and not glossy.
Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain well. Cut up eggs and mix with macaroni.
Add all ingredients.
Add more dressing if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: make  ahead potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add all other ingredients.
Cool and store in the refrigerator for up to 10 days.
To serve, put desired amount in a buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: hole-in-one
directions: Very lightly butter both sides of the bread.
Put into a frying pan.
Using a round cookie cutter, a biscuit cutter or the open end of a glass, make a hole in the center of the bread slice. Turn the heat on under the pan low.
When pan is warm and bread starts to toast, break an egg into the hole.
When the egg is fried on one side, carefully flip with a spatula and fry the other side until egg is done, but yolk is still runny.
You may also toast the "holes" while cooking the Hole-In-One.

title: grandma eloina's ham bread roll
directions: On a floured board, roll out the loaf of bread in a rectangle shape, until it has medium to thin thickness.
(When rolling, press down with your fingers and add a bit of oil.)
When the dough is rolled out as much as you can, lay out the slices of ham, covering the dough.
Add the green olives (sliced) and the red pimentos (without juice).
Add the capers and the raisins.
Fold the edges in a little bit, then start rolling the dough into a roll.
Seal the ends and sides with toothpicks.
Brush it with melted butter or with a mix of 1 egg yolk and 1 tablespoon milk. Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes, or until the bread browns.
Let it cool before cutting.
Cut it in medium size slices.
Serve as an appetizer or to accompany any meal.

title: penne pasta with broccoli(marinara sauce-toasted bread crumbs)
directions: In a heavy skillet, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until golden color.
Discard garlic.
Add crushed tomatoes, basil, parsley and oregano.
Simmer for about 30 minutes, uncovered, and set aside.
Boil broccoli just until tender; drain and set aside. Toast bread crumbs in a moderate oven or skillet with 1 tablespoon olive oil until golden, being careful not to burn.
Set aside. Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Do not overcook; drain.

title: plantation cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until pineapple juice concentrate is thawed and sugar is dissolved. Pour over ice cubes in tall glasses and serve garnished with mint sprigs or mix in a punch bowl. Add ice and serve in punch cups. Makes about 2 quarts before ice is added.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese and butter soften to room temperature.
Cream butter and cream cheese with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sprinkle a small amount of the flour over the chopped pecans.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans to other batter.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: hot rolls with cornmeal
directions: Cook cornmeal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk until thick over medium heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to mixture with 2 beaten eggs.
Let mixture rise for 2 hours, covered, in a warm place.
Add flour to form soft dough. Knead well and let rise again for 1 hour, until doubled.
Knead again and roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Brush with melted butter.
Crease and fold over like Parker House rolls.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in order given; blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Put on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with sliced strawberries and whipped cream.

title: apple pudding
directions: Grease casserole and place in it sliced apples or any other fruit desired mixed with sugar.
Pour over it the batter.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 45 to 50 minutes or until done. Good with cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: tasty 'n tender round steak
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Combine dry mustard, flour, salt and pepper; use to coat meat.
Reserve remaining flour mixture. Melt Crisco.
In skillet, brown meat, half at a time, on both sides in hot Crisco.
Push meat to one side; stir in reserved flour mixture.
Combine water and Worcestershire sauce; stir into skillet mixture.
Cook and stir until thick.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Drizzle gravy over meat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together in dish. Cover with 2 cups Ritz and 1/2 cup melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy carrot bake
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water for 10 minutes, or until tender; drain.
Combine the next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add carrots; toss lightly.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant.
Slice into fairly thin slices.
Dip each slice in egg mixture, then dip into bread crumbs to coat.
Fry in oil, gently, until lightly browned.
Put on paper towels or bag to drain.

title: rum walnut balls
directions: In bowl, stir together the wafer crumbs, sugar, walnuts and cocoa until well blended.
Stir honey into rum and gradually add to dry ingredients, mixing first with spoon, then your hands.
Add just enough rum mixture to make dough hold together.
Roll bits of the dough into small balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Balls will seem soft, but will firm up.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cook bacon and onion together in medium-size skillet over medium heat until bacon is crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon and place in ungreased 2-quart baking dish. Add green beans.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Baking time:
3 hours.

title: bean bundles
directions: Cut bacon in half. Wrap bacon halves around bunches of green beans. Secure bacon with toothpick. Place bean bundles in oven-safe dish. Make glaze with other two ingredients. Pour glaze over beans. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled eggs and ham
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with fork. Add all remaining ingredients and mix together in bowl. Fill egg whites with mixture, heaping it lightly. Arrange on serving tray. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate until serving time. Do not keep longer than 24 hours.

title: michelle's cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6
ingredients. Form into ball. Refrigerate. Roll in a second cup chopped nuts before serving. Can be divided. Can be frozen.

title: pommes anna
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into paper-thin slices.

Brush bottom and sides of a 6 1/2 x 3-inch souffle dish generously with butter. You may also use a round deep casserole dish and cover with foil or a specially designed copper pan that's made specifically for this dish that you can get at specialty stores.
Arrange potatoes, overlapping slices, around edges of pan to form a firm wall, then place an overlapping layer of potatoes in the bottom of the dish to cover.
Brush lightly with butter and sprinkle lightly with onion, salt and pepper.
Repeat the layers until all ingredients are used, then cover lightly with foil.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 30 more minutes until top is browned.
Unmold on platter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot honey ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Pour over rolls and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Debone and set aside. Empty 3 cans of cream of chicken soup in large bowl.
Add small container sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add deboned chicken breasts.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. In small bowl, crush Ritz crackers and add melted butter. Sprinkle this on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: our favorite lettuce salad
directions: In a large bowl, tear up a layer of lettuce.
Top with some onion slices.
On top of this, slice some black olives and chunks of Swiss cheese.
Crumble some bacon on this.
Glob 3 or 4 spoonfuls of mayo and sprinkle with sugar.
Make about 3 layers. Do not stir!
Refrigerate.
Before serving, dribble with hot bacon grease.

title: mexican style macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Saute onions in oil, then stir in chili powder. Add ground beef, browned, to macaroni. Sprinkle cheese on top after other ingredients are added.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: real texas chili
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart kettle over medium heat. Add beef, stirring frequently with wooden spoon, until meat changes color but does not brown. Lower heat; stir in garlic. Combine chili powder, cumin seed and flour. Sprinkle meat with chili mixture, stirring until meat is evenly coated. Crumble oregano over meat. Add 1 1/2 cans broth and stir until liquid is blended. Add salt and pepper. Bring to boil and stir occasionally. Reduce heat for 1 1/2 hours and stir occasionally. Add remaining broth and cook 30 minutes longer until meat almost falls apart. Cool thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate overnight to ripen flavor. Reheat chili in top part of double boiler.

title: salsa
directions: Cook in large kettle for 3 hours.
Process in pint jars for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Mix the soda in the sour cream.
Add salt to flour.
Add sour cream and flour alternately to sugar mixture, beating well.
Pour into greased and floured 16-inch loaf pan or tube pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar. Add drained canned fruit. Mix in the rest of the ingredients. Sprinkle with cinnamon as desired. This uses 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans, but can be made as 1 large casserole in a lasagna size pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar; press onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Combine softened cream cheese and cup of sugar.
Mix well and fold in whipped topping.
Spread on pretzels and chill.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and chill until partly jelled. Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: ala pilaf
directions: Melt margarine; add Ala and vegetables.
Stir until tender and Ala is browned.
Add seasonings and bouillon.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Can add grated carrots, chopped peanuts, raisins or green pepper and olives.
Ala is cracked wheat.

title: tropical pie
directions: Recipe fills 2 pie shells.

title: bread and fruit pudding
directions: Soak the raisins in hot water to cover for 15 minutes; drain. Soak the bread in 2/3 cup milk for 2 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the eggs, 1/2 cup milk, salt, sugar, lemon rind, flour and cornmeal; blend well.
Add the apples, pear, grapes and drained raisins.
Generously butter a 10-inch cake pan.
Lay soaked bread in pan and pour batter over, arranging fruit evenly. Sprinkle with rosemary, 2 tablespoons sugar and drizzle with olive oil.
Bake for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve pudding lukewarm or lightly reheated.

title: cornbread dressing and gravy
directions: Boil chicken broth.
Break up egg bread, crackers, herb dressing mix.
Add celery, onions, soup, eggs.
Pour hot chicken broth over mixture and let stand 30 minutes or more.
Mix well, using as much chicken broth as needed to make real moist.
Salt to taste.
Bake in large pan one hour and 45 minutes on 375 degrees. May take longer.
Bake until nice and brown.
Serve with gravy on side (recipe follows).

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in very small amount of warm water, stirring it to make it work.
Add rest of water, yeast and mix into dry ingredients.
Knead well.
Let raise to double.
Make into dinner rolls or buns.
Let raise to double and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad with asparagus
directions: Place chicken in center of a large square of aluminum foil. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Wrap and cook in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool and remove meat from bone. Cut into bite-size pieces.
In a large bowl, add chicken, peas, asparagus and mushrooms.
Mix together the yogurt, mayonnaise, dill weed, salt and pepper and gently combine with other ingredients.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: our favorite chicken pie
directions: Prepare the peas, carrots and mushrooms.
Mix with chicken in 10 x 13-inch baking dish and pour over the soup, mixed with broth. Season with pepper.
Mix flour, butter and buttermilk.
Spoon over chicken/vegetable mixture.
Bake at 400° about 40 minutes.

title: bread pudding with rum sauce
directions: Tear bread into 1-inch pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs in mixing bowl with 1 cup sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, raisins and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over bread. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve Rum Sauce over pudding.

title: caramel layer brownies
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup of milk and nuts.
Mix by hand until it holds together.
Press half of mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and eggs well. Add flour gradually, beating well. Add vanilla, apples, cinnamon and nuts (if using). Mix ingredients well. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or any tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°. Let cool about 30 minutes, then turn into cake plate.

title: play soap bubbles
directions: Mix and blow through little wire screens or circles.

title: faye goldstein's cheesecake
directions: Cut butter into crumbs with pastry cutter and press into a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes.

title: patsy's special taco salad
directions: After browning the ground beef, add the can of beans and simmer for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, shred the lettuce and add onion, tomatoes and grated cheese.
Toss together, combine lettuce and beef mixtures with a 6 oz bag of crushed Fritos and toss with one 8 oz bottle of Catalina salad dressing.
Serve immediately.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in plastic wrap with sake. Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes. Make sure that chicken is thoroughly cooked. Cool. Shred cooled chicken by hand into bite-size pieces. Pour dressing over chicken and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Mix chicken and lettuce. Serve cold.

title: buster bars
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with the melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spread softened ice cream over crust and sprinkle with peanuts.
Melt the other 1/2 cup margarine and add the chips, sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool and spread on top of peanuts. Freeze until firm. To serve, cut into bars.

title: chili (texas)
directions: Chop onion.
In large 8-quart pan, cook chuck; remove all grease.
Add all ingredients and simmer until well blended, 4 hours or until tomatoes are cooked down.
It's overcooked if chuck loses its coarse texture.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fresh lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions.
Add dry Jell-O to mixture. Use Pam to spray a 3 x 11 x 9-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter.
Grease bottom of baking dish or sheet cake pan and spread 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of pan.
Cream package of cream cheese with sugar.
In another bowl, mix milk and Dream Whip and beat until stiff.
Combine with cream cheese mixture.
Spread half of this mixture on top of crumbs.
Add cherry pie filling for the next layer.
Spread other 1/2 of cheese mixture on top of cherries.
Add other half of crumbs for last layer.
Chill overnight.

title: barbecued pork tenderloin
directions: Cut tenderloin into 8 slices and dredge with flour.
Cook in the shortening in a skillet until brown.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the pork.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, turning pork occasionally.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites stiff (add cream of tartar before beating). Add sugar and blend well.
Add crumbled wafers and nuts (blend, do not beat).
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes (do not overbake).
Allow to cool completely.
Press down with egg turner.
Prepare Dream Whip and pour on base.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Serves about fourteen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: apple pan betty
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, saute apple in margarine until tender, about 2-3 minutes. Add bread cubes. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon; mix well. Saute until bread is warmed. Serve immediately.
2 servings.

title: mr. cole's marinated grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken breasts.
Pour into a 1-gallon Ziploc bag.
Add chicken breasts; shake and seal, removing as much air as possible.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove chicken breasts from marinade sauce; grill to taste.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix together and sprinkle bread crumbs with pats of butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon raisin muffins
directions: In a medium bowl combine flour, cream of wheat, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In a small bowl combine milk, egg, oleo and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon mixture into a greased muffin pan.
Makes 12.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; brush tops with fruit juice and roll in remainder of sugar. Good without sugar also.

title: chicken nibbles
directions: Cut chicken pieces as desired.
Put chicken in a small bowl with milk.
Combine remaining ingredients in a plastic bag.
Add 3 to 4 pieces of chicken (shaking off excess liquids).
Shake bag to coat chicken well with crumbs.
Place on a greased baking sheet. Be sure the pieces are not touching.
Repeat with the remaining chicken.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown. Remove and serve plain or with sauce.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soups, chicken, broth, chilies, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Set aside. Place layer of 4 tortillas in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon layer of chicken mixture until covered.
Add a layer of cheese. Repeat to make three layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Mix broth in mixture until soggy.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until it is still "wet looking."

title: sweet and pungent chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layers in baking dish.
In saucepan mix together remaining ingredients, except tidbits, but use the juice.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Brush all sides of chicken.
Cover and bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes more, brushing often.
Add tidbits to sauce; heat 3 minutes.
Pour over chicken on serving plate and serve.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Melt butter.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add egg, buttermilk and butter to flour.
Stir lightly.
Batter should be thick, spongy and puffy.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on griddle. Makes 16 to 18 (3 1/2-inch) pancakes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Place in a greased casserole.
Set casserole in a pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes uncovered.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown sausage and onion with garlic powder and Creole seasoning for 1 hour.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese and chips.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar,
water and syrup in saucepan over low heat until sugar
is	dissolved.
Cook
until
candy	thermometer reaches 252°.
Remove
from
heat and pour over stiffly beaten egg whites. Beat
constantly
until
mixture
holds shape and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll out dough very thin on floured surface; let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up loosely; slice 1/4-inch wide. Unroll.
Let dry 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Wash and peel peaches. Cook sugar, vinegar, water and spices for 10 minutes. Add peaches and cook slowly until tender. Let peaches stand in syrup over night. The next morning drain
and cook syrup until it thickens slightly. Pack peaches in jars and cover with hot syrup. Seal the jars.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Make into balls and bake at about 400° in a single layer in a baking pan. Drain off grease and place in casserole. Cover with tomato sauce and place in 300° oven. Heat to simmer.

title: spaghetti-lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; add diced onion.
Drain fat; add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer.
Cook spaghetti, then layer meat, cheese, noodles, meat, cheese, noodles, etc.
Last layer on top needs to be cheese.
Bake in a 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: chicken apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 5 servings. Contains 150 calories per cup.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease
an	8-inch baking dish.
In baking dish combine
berries,
cup
sugar,
cornstarch, 1 tablespoon butter, lemon juice
and rind and cloves.
In small bowl combine flour, remaining 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in egg,
milk	and
remaining 2 tablespoons butter until soft dough forms.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto blueberry mixture.
Bake cobbler 30	to
35	minutes or until topping is golden brown and filling bubbles.
Serves 8.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple; let gel.
Take pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Mix and cook until thick.
Beat Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Put Dream Whip mixture on top of Jell-O, then add cooked mix.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Mix ingredients
except
for
Certo and coloring.
Cook until it is a "rolling boil" for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add
Certo and
coloring.
Stir
well.
Pour	into sterilized jars.
Top each jar with melted paraffin and seal.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Stew chicken and remove from broth.
Put noodles in broth and boil until tender.
Pick chicken off bone.
Saute onions and pepper in butter until tender.
Mix chicken, Ro-Tel, cream of chicken, cream of mushroom, pepper and onions and spaghetti into casserole dish and top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Remove.
Place rice, water, bouillon cubes, butter and pepper in a skillet.
Cover.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture in casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top of mixture.
Cover and cook without stirring.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp cocktail(african)
directions: Place all ingredients except paprika in a blender.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth, scraping sides of blender frequently.
Heat paprika in a saucepan 1 minute.
Add spice mixture gradually, stirring until smooth and hot, about 3 minutes. Cool.
Mix 1 cup chili sauce and 2 or 3 drops of Tabasco sauce. Serve with chilled, cooked shrimp.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken in electric skillet until tender.
Add dressing mix, rice, water, butter and orange juice.
Simmer until rice is tender.

title: deirdre's lasagna
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Add ground beef and seasonings; stir beef to crumble and cook until beef is lightly browned.
Add tomato paste and water, mixing well. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.

title: passover macaroons
directions: Melt chocolate chips and bitter chocolate; beat egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Add rest of the ingredients; drop by spoonfuls on greased wax paper on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Place bacon in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Brown slightly in 450° oven.
Do not drain.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Smash biscuits flat or
roll
them out a little.
Place small amount of chicken and cheese in middle of biscuit.
Fold biscuit over and press
ends
together like a turnover.
Place in ungreased glass baking dish. Mix soup, milk and the remaining cheese and
chicken together.
Pour over Chicken Roll-ups. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pasta and cheese toss
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In a large skillet, brown ham in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add cream, egg yolks, cheeses and paprika.
Blend until smooth.
Toss pasta and pimentos with sauce over medium heat.
Salt and pepper to taste. Total calories for the recipe:
673 per serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yogurt-cucumber refresher
directions: Season according to taste.
Combine all ingredients and serve. Better if allowed to chill several hours so flavors can blend. Serve as a side dish to a meal or by itself.
Makes approximately 4 cups.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, butter or margarine, thyme and pepper seasoning in small bowl.
Sprinkle the chickens with salt and pepper.
Place chickens, bone side down, on the grill over hot coals.
Brush with the basting sauce.
Grill for 40 minutes, turning over once.
Baste frequently with the sauce.
Serve with the remaining basting sauce poured over the chickens.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together cornmeal, eggs, milk, soda, salt, creamed corn and drippings in mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Saute ground beef and drain off grease.
Grate cheese.
Chop onion and chilies and place in separate mounds.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a large black iron skillet.
Heat.
Sprinkle a small amount of cornmeal in skillet and let it brown.
Pour 1/2 cornmeal batter in skillet. Sprinkle cheese evenly over batter.
Next, ground beef, onion and then the chilies.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: no-knead crescent rolls
directions: Add sugar, oil, salt and cold water to scalded milk.
When mixture is lukewarm, add yeast and beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Gradually add flour, mixing well.
No kneading is necessary.
Can be mixed with electric mixer, if desired.
Cover the bowl with waxed paper and a towel; let rise until doubled. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts.
Roll into circles about 1/2-inch thick on a floured board.
Cut each circle into 12 wedges and roll into crescents.
Place on greased baking sheets and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Butter tops while warm.
Makes 3 dozen.
(This also makes delicious cinnamon rolls.)

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt together caramels, butter and milk. Prepare cake mix according to directions on box. Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

(Don't overbake.) Pour on caramel mixture. Break up Hershey bars; sprinkle on batter. Top with nuts. Pour on remaining 1/2 batter. (Pan will be full.) Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: no fail oil pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together; press out in pie plates or can be rolled between wax paper.
Double for 2-crust pies.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Punch holes with knife while still warm.
Spread pineapple, undrained, on top of cake. Mix cream cheese, pudding, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth. Spread on top of pineapple.
Mix Dream Whip as directed; spread on top of pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Gradually add milk and eggs.
Add grated sweet potato, lemon juice and butter. Mix well and pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese and the onion in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted into center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted (2 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Mix cheese and broccoli.
(Optional:
Add bacon, cooked and crumbled or onion.)
Pour into crust.
Mix eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over pie; mix gently.
(Put cookie sheet under pie for overspills.)
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes before serving.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: In a large pitcher, combine lemon juice and sugar.
Stir to dissolve the sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients and blend well. Makes about 6 (8 ounce) servings.

title: turkey crunch
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add green pepper, celery, 1 cup chicken broth, soy sauce, mushrooms, salt, and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer 5-7 minutes (may be cooked longer if you prefer vegetables to be soft).
Add turkey (chicken may be used) and broth and cornstarch mixture.
Stir well and cook until thickened.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: macaroni salmon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise for desired consistency.
May use chicken instead of fish.

title: grandma darrow's molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses and beat well.
Sift and measure flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Sift twice. Add flour mixture gradually with milk.
Add vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 10 or 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: whipped potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes so that they can be mashed easy.
Drain off water very well. Fry bacon and all chopped ingredients and saute it.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Mix topping well until the crumbs are coated with butter. Bake in oven at 350°
until bubbles and browned slightly.

title: asparagus loaf
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with strip of aluminum foil. Butter well.
Saute crackers in butter until golden brown.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper and onion.
Add cooked asparagus and sauteed crackers.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve as is or with hot chicken gravy, hot cheese sauce or canned mushroom soup, diluted with 1/3 cup milk.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Add chocolate and stir constantly over very low heat until melted.
Pour into a small mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended for a fudge-like consistency, beat only until ingredients are blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Chill until spreading consistency (10 to 15 minutes).

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Stir together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter; reserve 1/4 cup.
Put remaining mixture onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange uncooked broccoli over crumbs; sprinkle the Swiss cheese over the broccoli.
In an electric blender, whirl together the eggs, milk and baking mix until smooth; slowly pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until puffed and brown, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice krispies caramel bars
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter and marshmallows in microwave.
Add Rice Krispies.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread Rice Krispies mixture in pan.
Press down well.
Remove the Rice Krispies mixture out of the pan and put on wax paper.
Repeat method, except keep that mixture in pan (do not need to butter pan again). Sprinkle a layer of marshmallows over Rice Krispies.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.

title: shrimp dip ball
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into ball.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Serve with crackers.

title: brown seafoam
directions: Cook the brown sugar and 1 cup of water until it reaches 258°. While this is cooking, beat the 2 egg whites until they form a stiff peak.
When the brown sugar reaches 258°, pour slowly into egg whites.
Make sure you pour it in small amounts and very slowly, or you will cook your egg whites.
Add the vanilla flavoring.
Keep beating until the mixture forms a peak and the glossiness is gone.
Spoon by the spoonful into cupcake liners and top with pecans, if you wish.
For best results, use a glass bowl to mix in, the metal stays too hot and will not let the candy cool properly.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with spoon until batter is well blended and smooth.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and the nuts.
Spread in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup chips.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until set.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: b~b~q ribs
directions: *This sauce should be enough to cover about 3 racks of baby back ribs.

title: creamy fruit salad mold
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add gelatin. Stir until dissolved.
Cool; add 2/3 cup undiluted evaporated milk. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Blend in fruits and nuts.
Chill remaining 1/3 cup undiluted evaporated milk in refrigerator tray until ice crystals form around edges of tray. Whip until stiff (about 2 minutes).
Add lemon juice and whip until very stiff (about 1 minute).
Fold whipped evaporated milk into gelatin mixture.
Pour into a 6-cup mold.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and margarine for 2 minutes.
Beat eggs in casserole bowl and pour cooked mixture into it.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Place pecan halves on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix and bake 2 cups crushed pretzels, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 1/4 sticks margarine.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: butter frosting
directions: Mix and beat until smooth.

title: fish creole
directions: Arrange fish in 3-quart baking dish, thicker part to side of dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over fish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
After cake is cool, drip a little powdered sugar frosting (powdered sugar, Philadelphia cream cheese and vanilla).

title: festive barley salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients in order except the last 2.
Mix well.
Add black olives and tomato, then toss gently.
Let marinate an hour or so and serve.
Can be prepared ahead, just add tomato prior to serving.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over meat sauce.
Additional items may be added if desired.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: halloween cider
directions: Cut the apple into small pieces.
Pour cider into pan.
Heat the cider until hot.
Then pour into 4 cups.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons of drink mix to each cup and a dash of nutmeg and cinnamon. Sprinkle 6 or 7 apple pieces into each cup.
Stir and serve.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: In large pan combine 2 cups water, salt, nutmeg, sugar and potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer about 15-20 minutes or until potatoes are fork tender.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9 or 10-inch pan.
In a bowl, combine flour, oil, and 3 Tbsp. water and mix together with hands.
Roll out very thinly on floured surface.
Cut dough in strips and pinch with your hands and arrange over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: zucchini cobbler
directions: Combine flour, 2 cups sugar and margarine to make crumb mix. Put half of this mix in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Peel, core and slice zucchini into small pieces (8 cups).
Put into a cooking pot and add lemon juice. Simmer until tender.
Add to pot, 2/3 cup crumb mix, 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook until thick.
Pour over crust that is in the baking dish.
Add remainder of crumb mix and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan-cheddar dip
directions: Leave
cheese
at room temperature until well softened, then cream
together.
Add
remaining
ingredients
and blend well. This is best if made at least 1 day in advance.
A very rich spread.

title: japanese fruit cake pie
directions: Bake 50 minutes at 300°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fudge brownie cupcakes
directions: Blend sugar, flour and eggs by hand.
Melt slowly 4 squares and margarine.
Mix with sugar-flour mixture.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into foil cupcake liners.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: summertime cookies
directions: Mix chocolate chips and marshmallows into Cool Whip.
Spread about 1/2 inch thick on one of the crackers.
Cover with another cracker.
Repeat with all the crackers.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
No baking!

title: ham and egg crescent brunch pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in a 12-inch pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press into pan to form crust.
Press 1/2 inch up sides.

title: easy minute steak
directions: Cut up onion and bell pepper and place on top of minute steak. Place 1 strip of bacon on top and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add cheese and let melt before serving.

title: denver biscuits
directions: Mix dry yeast, milk, sugar, Crisco oil and 4 cups of flour. Mixture should look like pancake batter.
Let rise until double in size.
After the batter has risen, add baking powder, soda, salt and 2 to 4 cups of flour.
Flour board; roll and cut out like biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise awhile; freeze.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Makes 60 biscuits.

title: papoose pond pancakes
directions: Measure ingredients into medium sized mixing bowl.
Mix ingredients thoroughly with a wire whisk.
Cook on a 375° griddle until surface bubbles and then flip.

title: chicken salad(weight watchers)
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except tomatoes and lettuce; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, at least 1 hour.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Place squash, cut side down, in a baking pan with a small amount of water and bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or almost tender.
Saute apples and celery in butter for 5 minutes. Stir in crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Fill squash hollows with the apple mixture and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, or until squash is tender.

title: chicken crescent
directions: Cook
chicken,	sage,
salt
and
pepper
until tender. Remove from bone
and
cut
up
coarsely.	While meat is still warm,
add cream
cheese
and
mix.
Chill
in
refrigerator. Divide crescent rolls.
Spread
them
on dough board and press out by hand,
making
each

large	enough to hold a portion of chicken. Put a scoop of chilled chicken mixture in each piece of dough and roll up, stretching dough to seal in the chicken. Dip in melted margarine,	covering all over.
Roll in crushed stuffing mix. Place
on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes
or until golden brown.
Serve with gravy made from chicken broth. Makes 8 to 16 servings.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place warm
water
in bowl.
Add dry milk and mix well. Add sugar; mix until smooth.
To help dissolve sugar, set bowl in a pan
of
hot
water.
Use
in recipe as you would canned sweetened condensed milk.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers. ENJOY!

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in bacon drippings.
Combine egg, buttermilk and soda; mix well. Stir into flour mixture, mixing well.
Cut each frankfurter into 10 pieces.
Dip frankfurter sections into batter, covering completely.
Drop into 3 to 4 inches deep hot oil (375°) and cook until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Insert party picks and serve immediately.
Serve with mustard, ketchup or picante sauce.

title: gladys' red velvet cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Combine cocoa and food coloring and blend to a paste.
Add to shortening mixture; blend.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, flour and salt to mix.
Combine vinegar and soda and stir gently into batter.
Immediately pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Served best with cream cheese frosting.

title: calico bean soup
directions: Wash beans, peas and lentils.
Place in large pot, cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain off water, then add 3 quarts water.
Add ham.
Simmer slowly 3 hours.
Add chopped onion, celery, pepper, tomatoes and chili powder.
Stir gently.
Add garlic and sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 hour more, add juice of 1 lemon.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Serve with hot cornbread.

title: peach pie
directions: Put peaches in bottom of pan.
Place bread slices on top of the peaches.
Melt oleo.
Then mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to mixture, then add melted oleo.
Blend together and pour over peaches and strips of bread.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: easy snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices, then into fourths.
Roll into cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Cook at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and pecans by hand and press into pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese until smooth and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, lemon or orange peel.
Mix well.
In small bowl, combine milk, oil and egg; blend well.
Add liquids to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool 1 minute before removing from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Fry the apples in butter and sugar until moisture cooks out. Let cool. Add cinnamon. Roll the biscuits into circles and fill with cooled apples. Seal the edges with a fork and place in medium hot oil in a medium size saucepan. Do one at a time.

title: miniature cream cheese cakes
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Place 1 wafer in each cupcake liner or muffin tin. Fill with about 1 tablespoon of mixture.
Bake.
Cool. Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil; drain.
Add all ingredients except macaroni.
Bring to a boil; sprinkle macaroni on top.
Cook for 20 minutes in electric frypan.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Mix soup and milk in bowl; add vegetables.
Put in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer sliced cheese on top of casserole and then add croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together with wire whip and place in a greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange gumdrop cake
directions: Chop pecans, dates and candy.
Combine with coconut.
Pour melted butter over and let stand while preparing batter.

title: one million calorie dessert
directions: Place milk in top of a double boiler.
Bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chips melt and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows.
Chill.
Mix slightly. Brown coconut in melted butter.
Remove from heat.
Add crushed cookies.
Stir well.
Press 3/4 of cookie mix in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut ice cream into slices about 1/4-inch thick. Place half of the ice cream slices on top of the cookie mix.
Pour half of the marshmallow mix over ice cream.
Repeat layers with remaining ice cream and marshmallow mix.
Sprinkle top with remaining cookie mix.
Cover and freeze until firm.

title: chicken-in-a-garden
directions: Combine chicken, 1 tablespoon oil, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch, 1 clove garlic (chopped small) and pepper; stir well and let stand 20 minutes.
Pour remaining 2 tablespoons oil around top of preheated wok, coating sides.
Heat at medium-high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add green and red peppers and 1 clove garlic (chopped small) and stir-fry for 4 minutes.
Add celery, scallions, pea pods and 1 clove garlic (chopped small) and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables from wok and set aside.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, and mix with electric mixer.
This makes a big recipe, so I cut mine down to the smaller jar.

title: sugarless pumpkin pie
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together.
Mix all spices and combine with pumpkin mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cook and drain bacon.
In a large kettle (Dutch oven) use 1 tablespoon bacon drippings to saute onion, pepper and celery.
Add all remaining ingredients into Dutch oven, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Crumble and sprinkle bacon over each serving.
Serves 6 to 10.
Delicious in the winter time!!

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave and gradually add other ingredients; mix.
Serve as dip with chips or crackers.

title: glazed ham
directions: Wash ham and trim excess fat and skin.
Baste with both sauces, sprinkle pepper lightly.
Baste with honey.
Use toothpicks to place onion slices on ham. Then put pineapple slices on top of onions.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, then remove and turn ham over.
Put onions and pineapple on other side and baste.
Cook until tender and done.

title: peanut butter and chocolate squares
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
In saucepan, melt only 1 1/2 sticks butter.
Add to graham cracker crumb mixture.
Add peanut butter.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt remaining butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm, overnight is good.
Let stand 1/2 hour at room temperature before cutting.

title: chicken funny breads
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth; add salt, pepper, milk, onions, celery and mushrooms.
Mix well; add chicken.
Mix well, separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles (don't separate them by the perforated edges).
Put 1/4 of mix into center of roll.
Pull up corners and seal at top.
Seal sides shut with a press of the dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: poor folks apple pie
directions: Make biscuit dough.
Pinch off a ball of dough and roll on floured board in a circle until real thin.
Press edges with fork. Cook until golden brown.
Use stewed apples or applesauce. Sweeten and use whatever flavoring you like.
I prefer spice.
Put the cooked circle in a plate.
Cover circle with fruit.
Add 4 or 5 circles.
Cover each with fruit.
Makes a good pie.

title: cocoa drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg together.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in mixture.
Chill one hour.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Place in preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost with thin white icing.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream cheese; add other ingredients alternately beating well after each addition until it is very smooth.
Pour into a spring-form pan that has been coated with margarine.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight before serving.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; slowly add flour.
Shape into balls. Bake on a cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 325°.
After completely cooled, roll cookies in powdered sugar.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together beef, onion, salt, pepper and half and half and shape into 6 thick patties.
Brown quickly in butter and remove from pan.
Add flour to pan and blend.
Add consomme (undiluted) and wine.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and it has boiled.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, parsley, mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste.
Return patties to sauce and simmer until done, about 30 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream in a can
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Put mixture into 1 pound coffee can.
Close coffee can with a lid.
Put 1 pound coffee can into a 3 pound coffee can with a lid.
Put crushed ice and one 6 ounce Dixie cup full of rock salt into 3 pound coffee can (surrounding 1 pound can).
Put lid on and roll back and forth on a flat surface for 15 minutes.

title: hot tamales
directions: Use chicken and beef (equal parts).
Boil until tender.
Grind together.
Add all the seasonings to taste.
Make a mixture of water, cornmeal (white plain meal) and salt.
This is the cornmeal mush.
Line shucks of tamale paper with mush, then add a small roll of meat mixture.
Roll up and tie ends with string.
Place in broth where meat was cooked, then season with button of garlic.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Combine 1 cup of flour with the yeast, sugar, and salt in a large mixer bowl.
Heat the milk with 4 tablespoons of the butter until very warm (120-130°).
Beating at low speed, gradually add the warmed milk and butter to the flour mixture.
Increase the speed to medium and beat for 2 minutes.
Beat in the eggs and 1/2 cup of the remaining flour.
Increase the speed to high and beat for 5 minutes.
Stir in about 1 1/2 cup of the remaining flour, or enough to make a firm dough. Turn out on a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and turn once to grease the surface.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from draft, until double in bulk, about 1 hour. Combine the corn syrup and 4 tablespoons of the remaining butter in a small saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth. Divide between 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Using 1/2 cup of the brown sugar, sprinkle half of it into each pan.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour. Serve with chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Fold in sugar, syrup and butter, beating after each.
Add pecans.
Beat egg whites stiff and add to mixture.
Stir in.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 300° for 40 or 50 minutes.
Yield:
Will make 2 (7 or 9-inch) pies.

title: broiled crab meat appetizer
directions: Mix all together.
Cut English muffins in half; spread mixture on muffin halves.
Put on cookie sheets and freeze for 30 minutes, then cut into 1/4 sections.
Keep frozen until ready to broil, 6 to 8 minutes.

title: apple slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and apples.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Allow to chill for about 4 hours, then add salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix together and cook to firm ball stage.
Add 1 cup black walnuts or pecans.
Beat until light in color.
Pour into buttered dish and cool before cutting into squares.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Place shortcakes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut up strawberries in a large bowl.
Mix glaze and strawberries together.
Place strawberries over shortcakes. Spread Cool Whip on top and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat.
Add zucchini, vanilla and cinnamon.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir only.
Add nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello.
Add
lemon
juice
and pineapple.
Let stand until slightly jelled.
Add cottage cheese, nutmeats and marshmallows.
Let set, fold in whipped cream and chill.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine together all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Use 4 teaspoons per 1 cup of boiling water.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, water, sugar and salt. Stir in flour. Knead dough. Take a ball of dough about the size of an egg and roll it to 6 to 8-inches.
Shape into a pretzel. Brush beaten egg over raw pretzel. Put a generous amount of salt (kosher) on pretzel.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.
Don't overbake!

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 sticks soft margarine with 2 eggs and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Beat 10 minutes with electric mixer.
Spread on top of crumb mixture.
Top batter layer with sliced bananas.
Top bananas with drained, crushed pineapple.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and cherries on top.
Chill before serving.

title: oatmeal cake-amish
directions: Soak oats in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Let stand 2 minutes. Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Cream butter with vanilla.
Add both brown and white sugar.
Beat a lot! Add 2 eggs, one at a time.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add soaked oats and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: four layered dessert
directions: Layer 1 (Crust):
Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts. Spread evenly and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown; let cool.

title: reese's
directions: First Layer:
Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, brown sugar and 1/2 cup melted butter until crumbly.
Spread and press evenly into large cookie sheet with sides.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add sugar, eggs and oil, then add oatmeal.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix 4 dry ingredients.
Cream remaining ingredients and mix in dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water. Mix.
Cook and stir until thick and clear.
Stir in eggs.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/3 cup lemon juice, salt and oleo.
Cool.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine first five ingredients.
Add butter; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces.

title: giant chocolate chip cookies
directions: Place racks at middle and top levels of oven.
Preheat to 375°.

title: crazy cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt, then add sugar, egg, butter and vanilla.
Mix well by hand or use mixer.
Add chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, nuts and coconut; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: presto chili
directions: Brown meat and season to taste with chili powder.
Transfer to large skillet.
Saute garlic in olive oil for 1 minute, then add vegetables, cooking until tender.
Combine veggies with meat, tomatoes and beans.
Season with chili powder to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 8.
Top with shredded cheese and serve with oyster crackers, if desired.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Brown in skillet the ground beef and chopped onion; drain off liquid.
Add soups.
Cook spaghetti; drain and add to mixture. Mix well.
Pour in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Put 3 or 4 slices of cheese on top and place in oven until cheese melts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight (about 12 hours) and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nutri-grain crunchies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour this
mixture over the corn flakes and coconut.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch; cook until thick.
Add peach jello.
Pour over peaches.
Pour into pie crust and cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mash with fork, cream cheese; grated cucumber and minced onion and press out juice.
Spread on bread.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: tuna spread
directions: Drain tuna and flake until very fine.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spread 1 teaspoonful on small crackers, Melba toast or small rounds of toasted white bread.
If desired, garnish each with small piece of lemon or sprig of parsley.
Makes 1 cup, about 16 calories per tablespoon.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in fat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Makes two cups sauce.

title: carroll's cheese squares
directions: Cover a 7 x 11-inch baking pan lightly with Pam.
Layer ingredients in order given; do not mix.
Sprinkle parsley on top. Bake 20 to 30 minutes until set.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake in 2-quart dish 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: marinade for steak
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over steak which is in a bag or dish.
Cover.
Chill in refrigerator 6 to 24 hours, turning occasionally.

title: broccoli tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna, soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Heat until almost at boiling point.
Place layer of cooked broccoli in greased casserole; cover with layer of tuna mix.
Repeat and top with 1/3 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: doritos chicken bake
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Bone and cut into chunks.
Mix soups, hot sauce, chili powder and chicken stock.
Place in baking dish in layers as follows:
chicken, chips, onions, cheese and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt mary jane's coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Blend well.
Add coconut.
Pour into lightly greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Cook beef and onion in large nonstick skillet, stirring frequently, until brown. Drain if necessary. Stir in salsa, corn, water, and seasoning mix. Cook over medium high heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened and bubbly.

title: danish apple bars
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients, then pat half of the dough into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crushed graham crackers, then sliced apples.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Roll out the rest of the dough; place over apples. Beat egg white until fluffy and brush on top of dough.

title: skillet apple cake
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon and spread in bottom of skillet.
Arrange apple slices on top.
Sprinkle with walnuts. Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour into skillet over apples and cook over low heat 30 to 35 minutes, then invert.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside.
Cream butter and cream cheese in a large bowl. Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and salt, stirring until combined.
Stir in vanilla and remaining cup of pecans.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Thaw broccoli at room temperature.
Combine broccoli, onion, mayonnaise, celery, eggs and olives together.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours, then serve.

title: peggy's biscuits
directions: Mix.
Pour batter on floured board; knead.
Roll and cut out. Place on greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 20 to 25 biscuits.

title: chili con carne
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir once. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high:
5 to 6 hours).

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in the top of a double boiler. Add milk and egg yolks, beaten together. Cook over boiling water for 10 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from water; add 1 cup coconut, vanilla and margarine. Pour into a baked pie crust. Beat egg whites until foamy. Add sugar (1 tablespoon at a time), beating until sugar is blended and mixture stands in a peak. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl large enough to hold well. Let set in refrigerator overnight, covered tightly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Put into loaf pan and bake in
a 325° oven until done.

title: tomato dip or spread
directions: Mix soup, cream cheese and jello.
Heat until blended.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Stir in mayonnaise and almonds. May be molded or pour into a dish as a spread.

title: shrimp gumbo(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Saute chopped onions, celery and bell peppers in small amount of oil.
Boil shrimp as you would to eat; peel.
Make very brown roux of at least 4 heaping tablespoons flour and necessary oil. Add all vegetables to shrimp.
Add water as desired.
Season to taste and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Ham, boiled chicken or smoked sausage may be used instead of shrimp or may be added in addition to shrimp.

title: ole casserole!
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
After cooking turkey (frying) in pan, add tomato sauce, beans and taco mix; heat to bubbling.
Prepare corn bread mix according to package directions.

title: blueberry boy bait
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Cut in 2/3 cup butter or margarine until particles are the size of small peas.
Measure 3/4 cup of this mixture and reserve for topping.
Beat baking powder, salt and milk into remaining crumbs.
Beat for 3 minutes at low speed on mixer.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Spread in well-greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Arrange 1 cup drained blueberries over batter (fresh, frozen or canned).
Sprinkle with reserved 3/4 cup crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: caroline's cake with frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese-baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in the melted butter, then in the Parmesan cheese. Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in a shallow oven pan.
Place chicken breasts, skin side up, in pan.
Bake at 400° about 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Spoon drippings over chicken once or twice during baking.

title: drunken chicken marinade
directions: Mix all together, makes enough marinade for 10 to 12 servings. Figure 3 pieces chicken per person.
Baste chicken with marinade until chicken is done on barbecue.

title: pickled chicken(pescado en escabeche)
directions: Rub the chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in the olive oil. Arrange the slices of onions over the chicken and add the butter, bay leaf and vinegar.
Cover and cook over low heat until chicken is tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
In a casserole dish, layer broccoli, ham, cheese and 1/2 can of mushroom soup.
Put another layer of broccoli, ham, cheese and the rest of the soup.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly (about 30 minutes).
Top with Durkee French fried onions; bake 5 more minutes.

title: pickled carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, over medium heat, cook vinegar, water, sugar, mustard seed and cloves until sugar dissolves.
Add carrots; cook until crisp-tender.
Add green onions; cook 1 minute.
Cool; pack tightly into four 1/2 pint jars, arranging vertically for green and gold pattern.
Add hot vinegar mixture to cover; seal.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pints.

title: snowballs
directions: Drain pineapple. Combine cream cheese, sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well. Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Put mixture between two vanilla wafers. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and bake for 350° for 1 hour.

title: smoked sausage and bean soup
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces and saute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chester's jerky
directions: Cut meat into thin strips about 1/4-inch thick and 1/2-inch wide.
Mix ingredients in a large container that can be covered. Marinate meat for 24 hours in covered container, stirring at least once for the first 8 hours.
Place meat on rack in oven, smoker or dryer and dry at 125° to 150°.
Normally takes 6 to 8 hours.

title: sugarless bran muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sweetener; set aside. Measure cereal and milk into large mixing bowl, stirring to combine.
Let stand until cereal has softened.
Add egg and oil; beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring to combine.
Pour batter evenly into 12 greased muffin or paper lined cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix all other ingredients together, then mix with cooked carrots.
Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: dry roasted peanuts
directions: In a bowl, dissolve salt in water.
Add peanuts.
Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Spread on shallow, rimmed cookie sheet.
Bake in 275° oven for 1 hour or until lightly browned, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: nanny's fudge pie
directions: Mix together with mixer after melting margarine.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Bring pineapple juice and sugar to boiling point.
Add apples that have been pared, cored and sliced.
Cook slowly, uncovered, until tender.
Lift apples carefully from syrup and place in a bowl.
Mix cornstarch with 2 teaspoons cold water.
Add to syrup and cook to thicken.
Return apples to syrup and mix in.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Put in pie shell and sprinkle on topping.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients one minute.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla, pecans, coconut and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Then add quick oats.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto foil.
Cool.

title: peanut butter cream pie
