directions: Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter. Add whipped topping. Place in a 10-inch baked pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream 2/3 cup shortening and brown sugar.
Add Karo syrup and oatmeal.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Let cool and spread on bars.
Cut and serve.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Mix and place in buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Last 10 minutes, add crushed potato chips and paprika over top.

title: 5-hour stew
directions: Put all ingredients in Dutch oven and stir.
Cover tightly. Bake 5 hours at 275°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix everything except margarine.
Melt margarine in oblong pan.
Pour cornbread mixture into pan and bake until done.

title: biscotti
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and vanilla.
Mix flour and baking powder; crumble butter until it looks like rough bread crumbs. Then add liquid slowly; knead together until nice and smooth. Shape to your liking.
Bake at 350° to 375° (depending on your oven).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 4
ingredients together.
Pour into long pan. Mix nuts and brown sugar; sprinkle on dough.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin scones
directions: Sift flour and cream of tartar into a bowl.
Cut in butter. Add raisins, whole egg and enough buttermilk to make a soft dough. Mix and turn out on floured board.
Knead a few times.
(The less handling, the better.)
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch triangles or circles.

title: mexican lasagna w.w.
directions: Brown meat and onion in Pam-sprayed pan.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and picante sauce.
Stir until mixed.
In a small bowl beat eggs slightly, add cottage cheese.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 meat mixture, then 4 tortillas, then 1/2 cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 both kinds of cheese.
Repeat, ending with the shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheese bread in box oven or dutch oven
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cheese.
Pour half the batter in greased Dutch oven or 9 x 9-inch pan (if using box oven). Spread with half the cheese.
Add rest of batter and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 400° in Dutch oven or box oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir in cold water.
Cook until mixture is clear, stirring constantly.
While mixture is still hot, stir in jello and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool mixture in fridge until it begins to thicken.

title: pepper-onion relish
directions: Combine vegetables and cover with boiling water.

Let stand 5 minutes. Drain. Cover again with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes. Drain. Tie spices and hot pepper in a cheesecloth bag. Combine vinegar, sugar and salt. Add spice bag and simmer 15 minutes. Add vegetables and simmer 10 minutes. Remove spice bag. Bring relish to boiling point.
Pour boiling hot relish into jars.

title: chocolate chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar, until well blended. Pour into well-greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. When thoroughly cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: streusel topped sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes (if fresh) in boiling water 30-40 minutes or until tender.
let cool to touch; peel and mash potatoes. Combine mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, and next 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2 qt. casserole.
Combine brown sugar and remaining ingredients; sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and 2 cups hot water.
Add blueberries and pineapple (juices too).
Let set.

title: roasted peppers and onions in olive oil
directions: Broil the peppers on a broiler pan, at least 4-inches from the heat, turning them often, until the skin is charred and blistered. This will take about 10 minutes.
Place the peppers in a paper bag until they are cool enough to handle, about 10 more minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
For small gifts, place covers and tie calico over lids of baby food jars filled with the dry mix along with this recipe:
To use 1 tablespoon mix to a cup of hot water.

title: scotchies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, oats and coconut.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove immediately.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Put sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan and bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add the peanut butter, vanilla, oats and pecans.
Drop onto wax paper and let cool.

title: shamrock silk pie
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and flour.
Mix at medium speed with mixer until blended.
Add eggs, chocolate and Irish Mist liqueur.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into ready crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Put food coloring into some Cool Whip and spread over pie.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Remove skin; wash and dry chicken.
Place in gallon-size Ziploc bag and pour in dressing.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Turn often.
Grill chicken just until done.
Do not overcook.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons juice.
Mix juice with honey and Heinz 57; pour over chicken.
Bake 25 more minutes. Baste occasionally.
Place pineapple chunks on chicken; bake another 10 minutes.

title: corn and black bean salsa(rms conversion team salsa)
directions: Add drained black beans, corn and chiles in large bowl. Then add chopped tomatoes, avocado, and finely diced green onions. Finally, add finely chopped cilantro.
Stir gently and add juice of one lime.
Can be served with chips.

title: szechuan chicken with peanuts
directions: *Toast	raw
peanuts in peanut oil in microwave oven on High for
minutes,
every
3	minutes stir and check until toasted to taste.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package direcions.
Mix all ingredients, saving half of stuffing mix.
Mix with 1/4 cup of butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar, Pet milk and oleo in heavy boiler and cook on medium heat.
When it comes to a full boil, cook for 5 minutes. Stir constantly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together eggs, oil and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Fold in carrots, pineapple (drained) and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into cookie sheet, large one. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost hot cake with 1 small package of cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: reese cup pie
directions: In a medium size mixing bowl, combine pudding mix and milk. Whisk until smooth.
Allow pudding to set up 5 minutes, then fold in whipped topping and peanut butter cups.
Pour mixture into crust.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: raspberry-orange punch
directions: Mix and serve over crushed ice.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt and sugar.
After salt and sugar have dissolved, add remaining ingredients.
Make into rolls.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Cook at 350° until browned.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Cut margarine into flour until it looks like cornmeal.
Add cheese and work into flour mixture to form a stiff dough.
Shape into sticks.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Slice bananas into mixture. Add frozen strawberries and undrained pineapple.
Pour half the mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm. In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese with sour cream; add sugar. Spread over chilled layer.
Gently spoon remaining mixture (jello) on top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pecans on bottom; spread coconut on pecans.
Mix cake mix by recipe on box; pour over coconut and pecans.
Melt margarine, then cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy go lucky punch
directions: Mix all except ginger ale and chill. Add ginger ale to punch in bowl when ready to serve.

title: layered dessert
directions: Layer crackers in 9 x 13-inch dish to cover bottom.
Spread 1/2 pudding mix.
Repeat.
Lay crackers on top and frost.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: perfect fried oysters
directions: When the oysters are drained in a colander, place them in a bowl until ice cold.
Oysters should never be fried at room temperature.
Get your coating mix ready.
Have your deep fryer filled with enough oil to cover oysters.
The temperature should be 400°.
Then place oysters, whatever number of oysters you will fry in a batch.
Do not overload fryer.

title: ham ball
directions: Soften cheese and grind ham.
Mix all together and shape into a ball.
Chill.

title: abby's famous pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have pie crust ready.
In large bowl, combine corn syrup, sugar, eggs, butter, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into prepared unbaked crust.
Sprinkle with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set. (Toothpick inserted in center will come out clean when pie is done.)

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole, place rice, dry soup mix, bouillon cubes and margarine.
Bring water to boil and pour over these ingredients.
Stir until margarine is dissolved.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
If desired brown top under broiler when finished baking.

title: no fuss baked noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed using large pot.
Drain and return to pot.
Add cauliflower, broccoli, soup, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and cheese; mix gently.
Transfer to 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased baking dish and cover lightly with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil, turn oven off and let stay in warm oven 5 to 10 minutes more.
You may increase the protein level with leftover diced chicken, turkey, etc.

title: rice pudding(a hearty pudding that calls for instant rice)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat water to boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in rice.
Cover and let stand about 5 minutes.
Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Mix in rice and raisins.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle rice mixture with cinnamon.
Place casserole in square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour very hot water (1 1/4-inches deep) into pan.

title: catfish cakes
directions: Arrange catfish in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Drain and flake.
Combine egg, mayonnaise, mustard and next 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in fish.
Shape into 8 (2 1/2-inch) patties and coat with crushed corn flakes cereal.
Place on paper towels and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter log
directions: Mix powdered sugar and margarine until dough-like.
Spread out on wax paper very thin.
Spread peanut butter on top and roll into a log.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Slice and serve.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs that have been cut into strips about 1 inch long.
Lay on paper.
Bring water, vinegar and brown sugar to a boil.
Pour over spareribs in a casserole dish and cover.
Cook 1 hour in 350° oven.
Stir about twice during cooking.

title: quick breakfast donuts
directions: Make sure you only use buttermilk biscuits.

title: camp-out beans
directions: Cut sausage
in chunks and place in a saucepan with 1/4 cup of water;
cook
on
medium
heat until sausage is heated through, approximately
minutes.	Drain
off
grease.
Add beans, catsup,
onion,
salt
and pepper and cook on low until ingredients are heated through, approximately 10 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Spread frozen hash browns out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan, melt all the remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes; mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Bake for at least 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: delicious casserole
directions: Mix Ragu sauce with meat.
Layer in greased casserole 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of meat/Ragu sauce and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese and almond delight
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on bread.
Cut in finger-size open face or four squares or triangles.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes until edges brown.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup and milk.
Pour soup and milk into a double boiler.
Add chicken mixture.
Blend together. Cover, heat and serve piping hot on toast wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour
directions: Brown hot dogs and sausage for 15 to 30 minutes.
Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Add these juices with rest of liquids.
Add brown sugar and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons of cornstarch.
Add pepper, pineapple and cherries. Cook for 3 minutes.

title: broccoli and beans casserole
directions: Cook beans and broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Spread in layers in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Put chestnuts on top evenly.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Spread on top.
Melt margarine.
Mix with Rice Krispies.
Cover top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried vegetable medley
directions: Any combination of these vegetables may be used.
Slice vegetables or cut in 1-inch pieces.
For each pound of vegetables, use 1/2 cup corn meal, 1/2 teaspoon onion salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix dry ingredients and coat vegetables well.
Heat 1/4 cup oil in baking pan.
Add coated vegetables and bake at 400° until well browned (30 to 45 minutes), stirring occasionally.

title: amish oatmeal
directions: Combine dry ingredients, mix well. Combine egg with milk and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients with liquids. Mix well. Add melted butter, stirring in well. Spread in greased 9x13
baking dish, bake at 350° until edges are golden brown. Serve immediately with milk and with fresh fruit or chopped nuts, if desired.

title: breakfast meal in one
directions: Fry potatoes, onion and green pepper in large skillet with enough oil to barely cover bottom of skillet.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt oil and butter.
Add marshmallows and melt over low heat.
Mix peanuts, M&M's, and popcorn.
Pour melted ingredients over mixture and stir thoroughly.
Press into greased bundt pan. Cool completely (2 hours in refrigerator).
Remove and slice.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or lightly spray bottoms only with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine dry ingredients. Add combined banana, milk, oil and egg.
Mix just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender and drain.
Saute onions and carrots in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken soup, sour cream and stuffing.
Gently stir in cooked zucchini.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup stuffing cubes that have been tossed with 2 tablespoons melted margarine. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: seafoam icing
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar and vanilla together in the top of double boiler until well blended.
Place over bottom pan of boiling water and beat about 4 minutes, or until icing holds its shape.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening with brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. (Don't overbeat.)
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix. Add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Blend by hand.
Chill.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Over medium heat, stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Boil gently without stirring to 265° on candy thermometer (or hard ball stage).
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add vanilla, beating constantly.
Pour hot syrup in
a fine stream over egg whites. Continue beating until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into a buttered 8-inch square pan and spread evenly.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and layer in dish.
Place a slice of cheese on each piece.
Combine wine and soup and pour over top. Sprinkle stuffing over this.
Melt margarine and pour on top. Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: almond dream bars
directions: Line an 8-inch square buttered dish with 9 graham crackers. Combine sugar, butter and milk; bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat immediately and stir in remaining ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup almonds for top. Spread apricot mixture over crackers in dish.
Top with remaining 9 crackers.
Press down firmly.

title: punch slush
directions: Stir and put in large container.
Freeze at least 10 hours. Take out of freezer 2 hours before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots just until tender; drain.
Put onion and green pepper in bowl.
Immediately pour drained carrots on top.

title: apple bean bake
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add peeled and cubed apples.
Cook until tender.
Add sugars; stir until sugars are melted.
Stir in salt, catsup, cinnamon and molasses.
Add beans; mix well to blend flavors.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for about an hour.

title: chicken italian
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/8-inch sliced and place on an 18 x 12-inch pan that is double layered with foil.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add peppers and tomatoes.
Lay chicken on top of vegetables and brush with salad oil.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Pack in a loaf pan.
Spread catsup on top of meat loaf.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of catsup.
Cut each slice of bacon in half and place on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain, serve hot.
Suitable for freezing.

title: binini bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in pan, then drizzle over chocolate and nuts.
Crumble and pat remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake for 20 more minutes at 350°.
Cut when cool.
Do not overbake.
They freeze well.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Blend the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Combine the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add to the first mixture.
Mix and shape into small balls.
Roll in a mixture of 2 teaspoons of cinnamon and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 5 dozen.

title: mamaw bill's boiled custard
directions: Scald the milk.
Beat the eggs.
Mix the cornstarch and sugar together.
Mix with eggs and 1/2 quart of the milk.
Then blend with the 3 quarts of scalded milk on the stove.
Cook slowly until mixture coats spoon.
Refrigerate a glass to chicken thickness. If lumpy, beat with electric mixer.
Add vanilla to taste, about 1 teaspoon per 16 ounce glass.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Spread on muffins. Broil until bubbly and brown.

title: venison stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in layers in a crock-pot. Cover with water. Cook on high for 7 to 8 hours.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine egg, broccoli, creamed corn, onion, salt and pepper. Melt butter.
Add stuffing mix.
Stir 3/4 cup buttered stuffing mix in vegetable mix.
Place in ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add egg to soup; blend in other ingredients.
Spread over broccoli in buttered baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: guacamole with green chili peppers
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and chill for a few hours.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve with taco salad or with toasted tortillas.

title: cherry topped icebox cake
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and cold milk, let stand 5 minutes, then blend in whipped topping. Spread half of the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and top with remaining pudding mixture.
Add remaining crackers.
Spread cherry pie filling over crackers. Chill about 3 hours.

title: cherry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and sift.
Combine eggs, milk, cherries and shortening.
Add to flour mixture, stirring only until mixed. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 30 minutes, according to size of muffin.
Yield:
1 dozen medium sized muffins.

title: maple nut topping
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Spread over doughnuts.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Save out 1 1/2 cans.

title: fruit mold
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Place into mold and pour gelatin over fruit; chill until set.
Yield: 4 servings. Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 9 g, fat 0 g, calories 24.
One-half cup serving = 1 fruit exchange.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Boil ribs until they are tender.
While ribs are cooking, mix barbecue sauce, Worcestershire and A.1. sauce in a bowl.
Place ribs in a large pan, then pour sauce mix over ribs. Make sure all ribs are covered. If not, baste.
Let set in sauce, about 30 minutes. Preheat grill.
Place ribs on grill and cook about 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake shrinks from pan or tests done with toothpick.
Cool in pan on rack for 5 minutes.
Invert on rack to remove cake.
Use a tube pan; grease with Crisco and flour.

title: cassie's popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and butter on stove until amber, then add water and soda.
Pour over popcorn in large bowl.
Butter hands; form into balls and place on waxed paper.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into frozen 9-inch pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pinch off pieces of dough; roll into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until golden brown and slightly dry.
Do not substitute butter for margarine, as the consistency will change.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen, depending on the size you desire.

title: sole amandine
directions: Wash and dry the fish fillets.
Dip first in egg, then in almonds and last in flour, cornmeal and crumbs mixed well together. After breading, refrigerate for several hours.
When the breaded fillets have rested, fry in oil heated to 375°, turning only when browned on one side.
Remove after browning to paper towels to drain fat.
Serve hot with lemon wedges.

title: winter soup
directions: Boil chicken (4 to 5 thighs) until done.
Combine cabbage and potatoes in medium to large pot; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, carrots, onion and celery.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crackers or hot French bread.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Pour 1 dry yellow cake mix evenly over top of first mixture. Sprinkle 1 package broken pecans over cake mix.
Slice 1 1/2 sticks margarine or butter thinly; place evenly all over and close to the edge of pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cool punch
directions: Pour equal amounts of ginger ale and 7-Up slowly over ice cream and sherbet.
Serve immediately.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Put milk and marshmallows in top of double boiler and bring to a boil.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour mixture in pan that has been greased with butter or margarine.
Let stay in pan overnight. Dip in hot water to dump.

title: ricotta cookies with chocolate
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 4 cookie sheets.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until frothy.
Add eggs, Ricotta, vanilla and almond extract; mix well.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, vegetables and chicken in a 9-inch square baking dish until well blended.
Top with the biscuits. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly around the edge and biscuits are lightly browned.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into ungreased muffin pan.
Do not use paper muffin cups.
Bake at 450° for 11 to 14 minutes, depending on your oven.
Add icing, if desired.

title: troy's "super bowl" dip
directions: Mix together in a super bowl all ingredients.
Serve at the Super Bowl.
Serves San Diego.

title: taters and onions
directions: Scrub the potatoes; do not peel.
Slice and stand vertically in line in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Slice the onions and put between potato slices at intervals.
Melt the margarine.
Add paprika, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Pour over potatoes. Precook in microwave 10 minutes. Bake at 400° until done.

title: finger paint
directions: Stir starch and cold water together until softened.
Place in a saucepan.
Add 2 cups boiling water.
Cook until thick; remove from stove.
Add 1 cup soap flakes when slightly cooled.
Beat smooth.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients; add flour. Cut with spoon and drop in flour.
Roll out in hand and place on greased pan.
Bake at 450° until golden brown (not necessary to let rise, but if time is allowed, it can rise).

title: monkey bread
directions: Take all frozen bread pieces or may cut in half the pieces. Place in tube pan.
Sprinkle dry ingredients on this, then pour melted butter over all. Cover with a towel and let rise 6 to 8 hours. This is good to fix at 10 p.m.
and bake at 7 a.m. for 30 minutes at 350° for breakfast.

title: beef roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Put all ingredients into 1 browning bag.
Tie end and cut slits into top of bag.
Set oven for 350°. Cook for 2 hours or until done.

title: lemon bars
directions: *I usually use 1 1/2 times this much.

title: grilled wrapped franks
directions: Pat franks dry.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes. Divide dough into 10 equal parts.
Pat 1 part dough around each frank with fingers floured with baking mix completely covering franks.
(Can be wrapped and refrigerated at this time up to 24 hours.)
Brush cooking grill with oil. Grill franks about 4-inches from coals until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: ham dip
directions: With mixer, blend cream cheese, Miracle Whip and sour cream. Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: one dish meal
directions: Cut beef steak into servings.
Place ingredients alternately in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in oven until done.
Serves 4 persons.

title: wiener hashed with potatoes
directions: Cut wieners into thin slices.
Brown in oil with onions. Add potatoes, water, salt, mustard, vinegar and celery seed.
Mix together and heat about 5 minutes.

title: ellen's celery bake
directions: Parboil celery until almost tender.
Drain and put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole with almonds and water chestnuts.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and stir until smooth.
Slowly stir in broth and half and half.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Add mushrooms, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Pour over celery. Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: great chocolate dessert
directions: Mix soft margarine and 1 cup flour; press into a 9 x 11-inch pan for crust.
Bake at 350°.
Let cool.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Mix soy sauce, water, cornstarch and vinegar in 2-quart bowl.

title: blueberry skillet cobbler
directions: Combine berries, water and sugar in a skillet.
Bring to a boil and simmer while you make the batter mix.
Mix margarine, baking mix and buttermilk.
Drop batter, by the spoonful, over berries.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana coconut bread
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt until thoroughly blended. In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vinegar mixture, vanilla and bananas.
Gradually stir in flour mixture just until blended; stir in coconut.
Pour batter into a greased and floured-dusted 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes until bread begins to pull away from sides of pan and a wooden skewer inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on a rack to cool completely.
Wrap and store for 1 day before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.
Good slightly toasted.
You can buy unsweetened coconut where health foods are sold.

title: betty's butterscotch pie
directions: Cook the brown sugar and water together to form a syrup.
Make a smooth paste of flour using a small quantity of milk. Scald remaining milk and add beaten egg yolks.
Combine slowly with flour mixture, stir to keep smooth.
Add syrup and place in top of double boiler.
Cook until thick, add butter and vanilla.

title: onion baked fillets
directions: Cut fillets into serving-size portions.
Sprinkle with salt. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix.
Dip fish into 1 cup of the mixture, then roll in crushed onions.
Place fish on a well-greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with remaining dressing if desired.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Then add eggs, sour cream, soda and flour.
Pour in muffin tins.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle mixture on top of muffins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Mix well.
Add salt. Cover and let stand 3 hours.

title: cha cha cha corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in large stock-pot.
Add onion and saute until translucent.
Add peppers and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add corn, cook for 10 minutes.
Add tarragon, chili, salt, pepper and sugar. Cook 2 minutes.
Add milk and water.
Bring to a boil and serve. Serves 8.

title: microwave enchilada casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and garlic.
Microwave at High until beef loses pink color, 5 to 9 minutes, stirring once to break up meat.
Drain.

title: strawberry shortcake biscuits
directions: Put
the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and shortening in a sifter, then rub together.	Add the milk.
Grease a 9 x
13-inch pan.
Drop by tablespoons into the pan;
they will spread out. Bake
in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch; browns easily.

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Cook noodles until done. Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix cocoa and coloring to make a paste.
Add to shortening mixture.
Add salt. Put vanilla in buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour; don't overbeat.
Mix vinegar and soda; blend well, but don't beat.
Bake in 2 layers, 9-inch, for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or 1 layer long pan 45 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Add cinnamon, salt, soda, rhubarb, nuts and flour.
Add milk last.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy hash bake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish with bread slices. Press hash over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over hash.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add the rest.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil.

title: chicken ala dressing
directions: Fry mushrooms in oleo for 5 minutes, then add to the chicken. Take one half of the chicken broth and make a gravy using milk to moisten the flour.
Pour the gravy over the chicken, being sure it makes the chicken moist.
Take the other half of the broth and add bread.
Fry onion in oleo and add to bread (I use celery with the onion).
Add salt, sage or celery and pepper.
Beat eggs real good and add to bread mixture.
Put chicken in a large long pan that will cut 15 pieces and pour dressing over the chicken.
Bake until brown in slow oven.

title: fudge pie
directions: Put butter and chocolate in pie pan in a 325° oven to melt.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken.
Heat oil in a skillet until hot.
Brown chicken on both sides over medium heat; drain fat.
Add sauce, water, garlic, onion and bell pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or spaghetti.

title: low-fat scalloped potatoes
directions: Put oil in pan, add flour and cook 30 seconds.
Whisk in milk until no lumps.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and cook until thick; remove.
Add pimentos.
Layer with onions, potatoes and cheese in 2 1/2-quart sprayed dish.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: breakfast sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble then drain.
Prepare 9-inch pre-made or "from scratch" pie shell.
Mix cheese and sausage. Sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Sift again with salt and soda.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add milk alternately with flour.
Add nuts and fruit.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let bread thaw and rise.
In a skillet, brown sausage, onion, bell pepper and jalapenos.
Drain liquid.
Roll bread dough flat on floured surface.
Place on slightly greased cookie sheet. Spread half the sausage mixture down center of dough.
Sprinkle half the cheeses over mixture, then repeat.
Fold dough over and tuck in ends.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place broccoli in 3-quart casserole and microwave on High about 12 to 15 minutes until tender.
Slice Velveeta cheese and place over the broccoli until covered. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs; top with slices of butter.
Bake, covered, 30 to 40 minutes until cheese is melted.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Clean and drain whole chicken.
Separate one whole head of garlic
into
cloves,
leaving
skins
on.
Add one cup of squeeze spread
inside
of
chicken
and one half of salt and pepper. Rub
inside
well.
Place
all the unpeeled cloves of garlic
in different
areas inside of chicken.
Peel and chop other
head
of garlic.
Rub
on outside skin of chicken with remaining
cup
of spread
and other half of salt and pepper. Cook
uncovered
in open
shallow pan at 375° until brown all over and legs pull away easily.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix well and form into balls.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked fish(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fish, vegetables and seasonings in foil.
Wrap tightly and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: sharon's crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add sauces and mustard.
Stir.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Grease casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients. Cook, covered, at 350° until bubbly.

title: roast beef sandwiches
directions: Oil bottom and sides of pan, then rub oil over meat.
Make slits in meat and put in garlic cloves.
Mix the remaining ingredients and rub on meat.
Fill pan 1/3 full of water.
Add 2 bay leaves.
Roast 1 hour at 350°, turn meat over and roast 1 hour more.
Cool enough to slice.
Then put in crock-pot with juice from roasting pan and one large onion, sliced and one large green pepper, sliced.
Cook 2 or 3 hours on high.
Serve on French buns with cheese.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and wet separately, then combine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: watermelon chiffon pie
directions: In medium bowl, work together flour and shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Gradually add water to form a ball.
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Line a 9-inch pie plate.
Decorate edge, pricking the crust side and bottom.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes or until slightly browned.
Cool.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, then cook until thick in a double boiler.

title: homemade crushed pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 20 minutes, or until it looks somewhat transparent.
Makes 8 pints.
Cool and freeze. Tastes like crushed pineapple!
Use for salads and desserts.
Good in all kinds of Jell-O, especially cherry.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: In a cast iron skillet mix oil and flour until golden brown to make Roux. Cook other ingredients slowly until vegetables are clear. Add about 2 quarts of water to roux. Let simmer for about an hour. About 30 minutes before serving add shrimp and cook until shrimp turns pink. Serve over rice.

title: party peanut ball
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature.
Blend well;
add the other
ingredients and mix well.
Shape into ball or loaf and roll in chopped parsley and chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix everything together well.
Put in a 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: night before egg casserole recipe
directions: Brown sausage medium; drain fat.

Cut the bread and place on bottom of an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish (2-inch sides). Sprinkle sausage on top. Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage. Whisk or blend for 1 minute the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frog eye salad(sounds terrible, but great!)
directions: Cook shrimp and cut up.
Shred head lettuce, fairly fine, and add cut up green onions.
Add shrimp and mix in Best Foods mayonnaise until salad is moist.
Add a little lime or lemon juice and pepper.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter each slice of bread on one side.
Grease a large baking dish.
Place 8 slices of bread in the pan, butter side down. Cover with grated cheese.
Place 8 more slices of buttered bread on top of cheese.

title: herbed potato bake
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain and mash well.

Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and garlic and cook until onion is soft. Combine the mashed potatoes, onion mixture, bread crumbs, parsley, 1 teaspoon of celery seed, Parmesan cheese, corn and egg.
Mix well.
Spread potato mixture into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika and extra teaspoon of celery seed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken marinade(one of the best marinades i've ever tried!)
directions: Mix all and add chicken parts.
Marinate a minimum of 2 hours before grilling.

title: aunt lill's schaum torte
directions: Gradually add sugar to egg whites and beat until very stiff; will stand in peaks.
Fold in vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 275°.
Serve with fresh fruit on top.

title: green punch
directions: Makes two batches.
You need to half everything.

title: ellen's cocktail log
directions: Saut dried beef and onion. Set aside. Combine cream cheese, sour cream and horseradish. Spread dried beef and onion on waxed paper. Shape cream cheese mixture into log. Roll in dried beef. Spread on crackers. Yield: 30 servings.

title: hazel's rolls
directions: Combine Crisco, butter, sugar and hot water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and butter and Crisco are very soft.
You may have to heat this mixture to get the butter and Crisco to dissolve.
Beat eggs in bowl and set aside.
Stir yeast in warm water in separate bowl; set aside.
When the butter, oil and sugar are cool, add eggs and yeast; stir.
Add salt to flour and gradually stir the flour into the mixture.
Add only enough flour to make it sticky, but not stiff.

title: black-eyed susans(a preakness must!)
directions: In tall frosted glass, add ice, liquors and top with lemonade. Sprig of mint is optional.
Sip and enjoy! Perfect for a hot summer day in Maryland.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Quarter, core and boil cabbage until just tender.
Drain.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain fat.
Return to skillet; add tomato puree and onion soup.
Mix well.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish.
Place a layer of cabbage leaves to cover bottom.
Spoon 1/2 ground beef mixture over that.
Arrange 9 slices of cheese over that.
Repeat the layer; reserve enough cabbage leaves for the top.
Place in 350° oven and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
This is a great make ahead dish.
Freezes well.

title: potato soup
directions: Clean, peel and chop the potatoes and onions.
Boil 4 potatoes and 1 1/2 of the onions in a large pot with water to just cover, adding butter and salt to taste.
Boil until fork-tender.
Pour remaining potato and onion in another pot and boil until fork-tender.
Save.
Drain large pot, saving 1 to 1 1/2 cups water. Mix with beaters or blender until creamy.
Add milk until soupy, up to 2 1/2 cups.
Blend until creamy and place back on stove.
Simmer about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain remaining potato and onion.
Add to large pot and stir.
Add garlic powder.
Garnish with parsley.
For creamier, richer soup, add a spoonful of sour cream to bowl.
Serve hot or cold.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, green peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt and cover with crushed ice.
Mix thoroughly. Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Remove garlic.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Fill hot jars to 1/2-inch from top and seal.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add aternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 80 minutes.
I top my cake with powdered sugar (lightly dusted over top).

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare baked pie crust.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour into pie crust.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, salt and cream of tartar.
Let boil for 5 minutes, stirring to form firm ball. Remove from fire and pour over stiffly beaten egg whites (slowly).
Continue boiling until mixture holds its shape. Drop on wax paper.

title: impossible green bean pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease dish.
Heat beans in 1 inch salted water to boiling.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix beans, mushrooms, onion, garlic and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients; pour over beans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: flounder with crab and spinach filling
directions: Pat fillets dry with paper towels and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread equal amounts of this mixture on each fillet.
Roll up from narrow end in a jelly-roll fashion.
Place fish seam side down in oiled baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 13 to 18 minutes or until fish just flakes.
Serves 4.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Stir in the ingredients and simmer for 2 hours, then serve with cheese (sliced) to top with crackers.

title: brownie carrot cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at low speed with an electric mixer 2 minutes.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into squares. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, chilies, 2 cups of cheese and sour cream.
Divide in half.
Mix chicken in half of sauce.
Place a large spoonful and roll in tortilla; place in a greased casserole dish.
Pour other half of sauce on top.
Top with
2 cups of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For best results, do not microwave.

title: ham 'n rice
directions: Saute onion in oil or margarine.
Add ham and saute, then add rice.
Stir for a few minutes.
Add the liquids; bring to a boil. Stir.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add frozen peas.
Stir. Cover and let sit for 5 minutes, then serve.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixed with 1 can water over chicken.
Layer with cheese slices.
Cover with Stove Top mixed with milk and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Stove Top mixture should be moist.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: apple and orange slaw
directions: In a large mixing bowl, toss together cabbage, oranges and apples. Combine mayonnaise and brown sugar. Pour over cabbage mixture. Toss again until well covered. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and chill at least 1 hour.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute cabbage, onion, flour, caraway seed, salt, pepper and paprika.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.
Return to heat, if necessary but do not boil.
Top with small crackers.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat whites of eggs until stiff; add 6 tablespoons of the measured sugar and continue beating until sugar is dissolved.
Put whites in refrigerator until balance of cake is mixed.
Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar a little at a time until well creamed.
Then add 2 of the yellows at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients. Butter should be at room temperature.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until lemon colored.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat more.
Add flour and mix well.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Combine pecans and marshmallows.
Set aside.
In a large boiler melt over low heat the chocolate Kisses and butter, stirring constantly.
When melted, add condensed milk and mix well.
Add marshmallows and pecans.
Stir quickly until well coated. Immediately pour into greased oblong Pyrex dish.
Chill until well set.
Cut in squares.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and flour; mix well.
Add vanilla, eggs, cocoa and butter.
Pour into an 8-inch greased pie pan. Cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch, then add syrup and water.
Bring to a full boil and cook until thick and clear (stirring constantly). Remove from stove and add 2 heaping tablespoons strawberry gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Arrange 1 quart of prepared strawberries in a pie shell.
Pour cooled sauce over berries.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 to 2 hours to completely set gelatin sauce. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, then stir in remaining ones. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: grosmommy's corn soup
directions: Put
corn in a saucepan; add salt, pepper, 1 tablespoon margarine
and
1 cup of milk for each serving.
Heat until it almost boils, then add bread crumbs.
Serve.

title: smiley burnette's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix in blender until smooth or use mixer.
Pour into container and store overnight in refrigerator.
Cook on hot greased griddle.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and boil in salt water until tender. Drain and then mash. Saute onions in butter and add to squash. Add bread to eggs and mush up. Add bread to squash and mix well. Place in margarine greased baking dish. Bake at 325 for 20 minutes.

title: ice cream jello salad
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add jello and stir until it dissolves. Stir in ice cream until melted. Refrigerate until hardens.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Save enough shortening or oil to grease your skillet.
Pour mixture in skillet.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: rich and beautiful brownies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and preheat oven to 350°.
Place chocolate and margarine/butter in heavy saucepan over low heat and stir occasionally until melted.
Add sugar, cream, salt and vanilla; stir to mix.
Remove the pan from the heat and gradually, one at a time, whisk in the egg and the yolks.
Stir or whisk briskly until as smooth as honey.
Pour this mixture over the bottom layer and smooth the top.

title: colcannon "irish"
directions: Boil the potatoes in salt water until tender.
Blanch the cabbage in boiling salted water for 2 to 3 minutes and drain. Mash the potatoes until fluffy. Beat in enough milk to make them smooth.
Place pan over low heat. Add cabbage and green onions. Add salt and pepper and serve very hot.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice into baking pan.
Pour onion soup over rice.
Add 1 cup of water.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Mix the cream of chicken soup with 1 can of water and spread over chicken. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add water as necessary to keep moist.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk; start and end with flour.
Stir in sweet potatoes and flavorings.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle almonds and coconut over bottom of pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: **frosted lemon jello
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice for frosting. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add pineapple and sliced bananas and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: spicy spinach salad
directions: Wash and tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Chill.
Prepare dressing by combining in blender all remaining ingredients except bacon and hard-boiled eggs.
Blend 30 seconds.
Just before serving, dice the egg and toss with bacon and spinach.
Pour dressing on top and toss again.

title: texas chewies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add brown sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to above mixture.
Add chopped nuts rolled in additional cup flour.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in greased 11 x 16 pan.
Cool in pan.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Combine the pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter for the first layer.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes in glass 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except noodles.
Cover and bake for 5 hours at 325°.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter the bottom of pan or baking dish.
Put peeled apples and 1/2 cup sugar sprinkled on top of apples.
Mix with fork the oatmeal, flour, sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Sprinkle this over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and crust browns, about 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: italian-style deli roll
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 15 x 10-inch jelly-roll pan with foil.
Coat foil with cooking spray; sprinkle with cornmeal. Coarsely chop provolone, roast beef, pepperoni and peppers.
On floured surface, roll 1 loaf dough into 16 x 10-inch rectangle. Sprinkle half the provolone, roast beef, pepperoni and peppers over top, leaving 1/2-inch border.
Starting from long side, roll up, jelly-roll style.
Pinch ends of roll to seal; fold under. Place, seam side down, on prepared pan, about 2 inches from long side.
Repeat with remaining dough, provolone, roast beef, pepperoni and peppers.
Place on pan about 2 inches from other roll.
Brush rolls with egg white; sprinkle tops with sesame seeds.
Bake in 400° oven until bread is browned and sounds hollow when tapped, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 3/4-inch-thick slices. Serve warm or chilled.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, the ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: chili con carne
directions: If using dried red beans, soak overnight.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Brown onion and green pepper in hot fat, then add meat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasoning.
Simmer 2 hours, adding water if necessary.
Add beans; heat thoroughly.

title: slovak cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Keeps well in refrigerator 1 to 2 months.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream the margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Stir in flour. Add vanilla. Beat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious.

title: pickled ring bologna
directions: Mix vinegar, water, sugar and salt in a 1 gallon jug (wide mouth).
Add more to your taste of any of the mixture if needed. Add in thirds to the mixed brine the sliced bologna and sliced onion rings.
Add the pepper seeds and chopped garlic.
Continue adding the ingredients until all is used up.
Stir well. Refrigerate and stir daily.
Will be ready to eat in about a week. Remove casing and slice into 1/4-inch pieces.

title: white coconut cake
directions: First, add Crisco and sugar.
Add egg whites one at a time. Add milk, flour and lemon flavoring.
Put in greased pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Do not open oven door while baking. Makes 3 layers.

title: peanut cream chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and 1 egg, at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sturgis family's dutch pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/8 cup water.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups warm water.
Add brown sugar and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Knead until smooth and elastic.

title: oatmeal white chippers
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat butter and both sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; blend.
Stir in dry ingredients. Add chips, oats and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together until they become crumbly.
Press 1/2 of the crumbs into a greased 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with rhubarb.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil, vanilla and 2 cups grated zucchini. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to first ingredients.
Beat well, then add nuts.
Bake in two loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: "slaw"
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Chill for about 30 minutes.

title: vanilla blanc mange
directions: In medium saucepan, slowly heat 2 cups milk just until bubbles form around edge of pan.

title: apple pie slices
directions: Make crust with flour, salt, butter, sugar, eggs and milk. Roll out 1/2 of pie crust to fit a large cookie sheet.
Crumble corn flakes over bottom crust.
Add apples to about 1 inch; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Roll out remaining dough for top crust.
Bake at 400° for about 50 minutes, until apples are tender and crust lightly browned.
Frost when cool with powdered sugar icing.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Chill all liquids ahead of time.
When ready to serve, put ice cream and sherbet in large punch bowl.
Now pour chilled liquids over this and mix well.
Have ice cream and sherbet in little chunks.
Great for weddings.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Combine dates and soda in hot water; let stand.
Combine sugar and shortening, then add eggs and beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to shortening and sugar mixture, alternating with date mixture.
Add nuts, chips and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch, well-greased and floured pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage. Crumble into small pieces. Drain grease. Add soup and salsa and heat until warm. Great with Frito-Lay "Scoops."

title: sara's rolls
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs; cream well.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add lukewarm milk.
Pour into potato mixture.
Add enough flour to make stiff.
Place on floured top.
Knead dough well; add flour as you knead.
Let rise in large bowl until double in size.
Knead again; cut rolls out. Let rise for 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: granny's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add orange juice and chill 15 or 20 minutes.
When mixture begins to set, stir in relish, pineapple and nuts.
Chill several hours or overnight until firm.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious meatballs
directions: Mix ketchup, water, cranberry sauce, sugar and kraut in saucepan.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: corn flake pudding
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put in greased baking dish. Dot top with butter.
Put in dish of water already warm.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: *spinach filling
directions: Thaw and drain well the frozen chopped spinach in a large pan. Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour into pan which has the first layer of dough in it.

title: mother's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in liquids and oil; let rise for 10 minutes.
Roll out and place in pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: golden cheese cornbread
directions: In medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in milk, egg and shortening.
Beat until fairly smooth (about 1 minute).
Add cheese; stir in.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: best ever caramel pie
directions: Melt butter. Add coconut and pecans. Cook over medium heat until coconut is lightly toasted. In bowl, mix Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese; fold in Cool Whip. Divide in half and layer into each pie shell the cream cheese mixture, the coconut, then the caramel. Repeat layers, ending with topping. Freeze. Will keep for weeks in the freezer. Thaw 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: apple waldorf salad
directions: Leave skins on apples; wash, core and cube.
Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all of above and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: french biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add butter and shortening.
Cut into flour until thoroughly mixed together.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add milk, then stir in flour mixture.
Mix to a good consistency.
Knead as little as possible.
Pat out on floured board and cut thick.
Put on baking pan. Bake in a hot oven at 450° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes two dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon. Pour into 2 quart casserole dish and put bacon slices on top. Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: super brownies
directions: Make pudding according to package directions but do not let set.
Add cake mix and chocolate chips.
Stir well and pour into greased 13X9 metal pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: five can
directions: Mix all ingredients well, leaving half of the noodles for top of casserole.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 2 cups bread crumbs. Form patties, gently rolling a small ball of mixture in the reserved bread crumbs. Place in freezer for 30 minutes to firm. Cook in vegetable oil just enough to coat bottom of pan for 2 to 3 minutes on each side at medium temperature. Patties will be slightly brown on the outside.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package.
I use a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.

title: mini party pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Brown sausage and ground chuck in large skillet. Drain well. Melt cheese into meat and add remaining ingredients. Stir until mixed well. Spread on rye bread slices and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly. Can be prepared in advance and frozen. Freeze on cookie sheet: remove to freezer bag. Remove as needed and bake.

title: low-fat pizza
directions: Layer ingredients in order on crust and bake at 350° until cheese melts and crust is browned.

title: pink champagne salad
directions: Mix crushed pineapple (drained very well) with cut up bananas and partially drained strawberries.
Then mix cream cheese with sugar until blended and add to fruit mixture.
Add large bowl of Cool Whip; mix.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Slice sausage in thin diagonal pieces.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover with water (about 1/2 inch above beans). Cook on high 1 hour.
Turn heat to low and simmer for 4 to 6 hours or until beans are tender.
Serve over hot, fluffy rice.

title: apple-cashew salad
directions: Break up lettuce, add chopped apples with peel.
Add cheese and cashews.
Blend olive oil, red wine vinegar, sugar, dried mustard and poppy seed.
Pour over salad when ready to serve.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Peel potatoes
and cut into sticks as for French fries. Arrange in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.	Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with onion salt and paprika.
Bake in a 450° oven
for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender and brown.
Turn
occasionally.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, tossing gently to coat.
Serve at once.

title: raw potato dumplings
directions: Drain raw potatoes well.
Add oil.
Saute onion.
Add raw potatoes.
Cook until forms a paste.
Cool.
Add riced potatoes, salt, eggs and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Shape into long thick roll.
Cut pieces to make dumplings.
Cook in rapidly boiling water until they rise to top.
Simmer a few minutes longer until cooked through to center.

title: lemon lush or three layer pie
directions: Mix butter or margarine with flour. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, then cool.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in seasonings. Blend eggs and cheese in bowl.
Stir in vegetables.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 11-inch quiche pan, 10-inch pie pan or 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread with mustard.
Pour in all ingredients.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
(If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil.)
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Combine onion with soups and broth. Also, add green chilies.
Add diced chicken and mix well.
Place layer of broken up tortillas, layer of chicken mixture and layer of grated cheese in 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt in crock-pot or pan on stove.
Serve with corn chips for dip.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese and salsa in a 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix 1 egg and butter into cake mix.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend remaining 3 eggs, sugar, cheese and vanilla. Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until light golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: lo-cal pumpkin custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into six custard cups. Place cups in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fill pan half full with hot water. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Contains 70 calories per serving.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball and roll in parsley flakes.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble fine (set aside). Brown hamburger in same pan.
Add onion and saute until tender. Combine the next 5 ingredients and pour with hamburger and onion into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Partially drain your choice of beans from bean list.
Be sure to use at least 3 cans but not more than 5 cans.
Stir into meat mixture, gently mixing.
Sprinkle with bacon and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Spread on muffin halves.
Place on cookie sheets and flash freeze.
Remove and cut each half in 6 to 8 wedges.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.
At serving time, remove the desired amount and place under broiler 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown.
Yield:
72 to 96 "bites."

title: best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, beat butter, sugars and cocoa until well blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
In small bowl, mix flour and baking powder together.
Stir into cocoa mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour mixture into greased or foil lined 8-inch square cake pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a cake tester or toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares and serve.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar until dissolved.
Add salt and celery seed.
Pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put in containers and freeze.
Good also just kept in the refrigerator to eat.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all the ingredients in big refrigerator bowl.
Add 6 1/2 cups sifted flour or 6 cups unsifted flour and 1 teaspoon salt. Cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight.
Make into rolls about 1 1/2 hours before you plan to use them and let them rise. Cook at 400° until done.
This dough will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: vidalia onion salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except onions), shaking well to dissolve sugar.
Pour over sliced onions.

title: risdon's frosting
directions: Grind raisins and set them aside.
Beat egg whites to a very stiff form, they will be ready for the boiling syrup.
Add sugar and water and boil until it makes a string when tested. Then while beating egg whites, pour the syrup into them and beat until they are fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Then add the raisins and vanilla and mix until all raisins are mixed in good.
Put on white cake.

title: quick clam chowder
directions: Chop bacon, celery and onion; saute until tender.
Add clams with juice.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add 4 diced potatoes; grate 1 potato and 1 carrot and add to boiling liquid.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add milk.
Thicken with flour and water mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk, sugar and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Put in cool place.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Boil enough hot water to cover hot dogs.
Turn off. Put hot dogs in pan and cover. Let stand 5 minutes. Drain water off.

title: lemon pasta basil
directions: Cook pasta according to box directions, omitting salt in water.
Drain and return to pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Put cream cheese and 3 tablespoons sugar in mixer bowl and let stand until soft.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, then sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish lined with crumb crust.
Bake at 275° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple wonder
directions: Combine flour, juice and sugar.
Mix in drained pineapple and grated cheese.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, using minimum cooking time.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain well. Combine with remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Chill several hours before serving.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: chicken in dijon mustard sauce
directions: Flour, salt and pepper cutlets; brown in oil and butter mixture.
Put in casserole dish, add wine to remaining butter and oil in pan, cook until glazed.
Add cream, whisk to light boil. Reduce heat and add mustard, pour over chicken, bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix together carrots, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured large cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: vanilla spiced icing
directions: Beat all the items until creamy.
Refrigerate until thick. Best if used as soon as possible after spreading.
Gets spicy if it sits for a long time.

title: squash jelly
directions: Cut the squash and boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain. Mash squash.
Add the sugar, pineapple and lemon juice.
Boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the Jell-O.
Seal in hot jars. Refrigerate before opening.

title: do-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes while hot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish and
put grated American cheese on the top.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit crisp(no sugar!)
directions: Mix apples, raisins, 1/4 cup flour, apple juice and cinnamon. Place in glass pan (9 1/2 x 12-inch).
Mix oats, 1/2 cup flour, germ, honey and butter in bowl. Crumble over apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken dorito pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix broth with both soups; cook until it begins to thicken.
Put half bag of Doritos (crushed) in bottom of deep casserole bowl.
Layer 1/2 of chicken on top.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over that.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add another layer of each ingredient; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 450° about 20 minutes to heat through and melt cheese.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Cream together with remaining ingredients. Place in greased ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: copper pennies(carrot salad)
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water.
Drain.
Add all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Trim brisket well and wrap in foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours. Bring other ingredients to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over drained brisket and bake 1 1/2 hours more.

title: larramie's lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Add next group of ingredients. Simmer uncovered until thick (about 1 hour), stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water.
Meanwhile, combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Place 1/2 noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of the cottage cheese mixture over noodles.
Add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Let set for about 1 hour.

title: feather dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, melted butter and enough milk to make moist, stiff batter.
Drop by teaspoons into boiling liquid on top of meat (sauerkraut with hot dogs on top). Cover, very closely, and cook for 15 minutes.
Don't peek!
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble crackers and mix with melted butter.
Divide in half and line the bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Heat soups, sour cream and chestnuts.
Pour half in pan and cover with chicken.
Add rest of sauce then chicken and top with cracker mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and serve hot.

title: homemade cornbread
directions: * J. T. Likes it kind of sweet.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in salt water until tender.
Add milk and butter.
Heat (don't boil).
Just before serving, add chopped hard-boiled eggs.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Mix biscuit mix and water to form a soft dough.
Beat with a spoon for 20 strokes.
Drop by spoonfuls into 12 medium ungreased muffin cups.
Press dough on bottom and up sides of each cup with floured hands.
Stirring frequently, cook ground beef, garlic and onion in a skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce; heat through.
Spoon mixture into cups; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: christmas punch
directions: Freeze cherries in their juice.
Combine pineapple juice, Hawaiian Punch, lemonade and water.
Immediately before serving, add 7-Up.
Float orange slices and cherries on top.

title: cutout sugar cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture. Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface.
Use cookie cutters to cut in shapes.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Decorate.

title: pam's baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger with onion.
Drain well.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and water, bring to a boil.
Cool, then add pineapple juice, lemon juice and enough kool-aid or food coloring to color you desire.
Freeze.
When ready to serve add 1 qt. ginger ale to each gallon of punch.

title: corn meal gravy
directions: Put sausage drippings in a 7 or 8-inch iron skillet preheated on medium heat.
Add meal and stir.
Add flour; stir
constantly until medium brown.
Add milk.
Stir constantly until boils to desired thickness.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: pollo en salsa(chicken in sauce)
directions: Rub butter over the chicken pieces.
Put in a frying pan with onion, salting to taste.
Cut the tomatoes in half and place on top of the chicken.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and let cook gently.
The juice of the tomatoes will make a tasty sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together applesauce and soda.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Frost with chocolate fudge.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat pineapple & sugar to boiling point.
Add jello.
Set aside to cool.
Mix dream whip according to pkg directions.
Add to cooled jello mixture.
Pour onto mold & refrigerate.

title: scalloped succotash
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and place in a shallow casserole. Combine melted butter and crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a light brown.

title: pan cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake in long cake pan at 350° until done (about 30 minutes). Cool and cut into squares.

title: vegan colorful spaghetti(serves 2)
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Heat oil in large frying pan and saute garlic and onion over medium heat for 2 minutes or until slightly golden.
Add tomatoes; stir and cook for 3 minutes.
Add spinach; toss with tomato mixture until spinach is just wilted.
Turn off heat.
When pasta finishes cooking, drain, then toss with vegetables over medium heat until coated.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugars, Crisco and egg thoroughly.
Add milk and vanilla. Then add flour, then oatmeal and chips.
Drop by small spoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Make a topping of crushed Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: zippy meatballs
directions: Beat egg in medium bowl.
Mix in bread crumbs, chili sauce, salt, onion, garlic powder, ground beef and celery.
Shape into small balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place in pan and cook at 350° about 20 minutes or until done.
Serve meatballs on wooden picks.
Dip in warm sauce.
May be made a day ahead and refrigerated or frozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with pumpernickel bread.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Combine egg, oil and applesauce. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake in nonstick muffin tins for 25 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Layer chicken and Swiss cheese in cakepan.
Combine soup and water and pour over top.
Top with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: ice cream sandwich delight
directions: Line the bottom of your Pyrex dish with ice cream sandwiches, then spread the Cool Whip on top of this, then drizzle on chocolate and caramel syrups.
You can top with cherries or chopped pecans. Put in freezer until ready to serve.

title: smoky mountain cheese dip
directions: Beat together the cottage cheese, cream cheese and milk. Blend in rest of ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
This is good with carrot, celery or cucumber sticks or broccoli florets and cauliflowerets.

title: spinach and bacon salad
directions: Tear spinach in bowl.
Add onion and garlic to 2 tablespoons bacon grease; brown.
Add sugar and stir.
Then add vinegar, oil and salt; heat to boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour hot dressing over spinach.
Add chopped bacon and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, no longer.
Let cool.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip; spread on pretzel crust.
Dissolve Jell-O and strawberries.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour on top of cheese mixture and chill.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg and add to mixture.
Add raisins, peach and plum preserves, dates, figs, nuts, citron and orange peel.
Bake at 275° for 2 or 3 hours or use your own judgment.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Grease 6 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Cover bottom of dish with 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Layer peas over crackers; layer with slices of cheese.
Dot with butter.
Add undiluted soup and onions. Layer again with slices of cheese and top with 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Saute beef, onion, garlic and green pepper until slightly brown.
