Add soup, water, salt, pepper, corn, beans and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Place mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon corn bread mixture over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french steamed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into long, thin strips as for French fries.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet. Add potatoes and stir to coat with oil.
Cover.
Cook until potatoes are well cooked, stirring often over medium heat. Add a little water if the potatoes seem too dry or begin to stick.
Season with salt.
Sprinkle with paprika to add color.
Stir again before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: no bake peanut butter balls
directions: In medium bowl, blend sugar and peanut butter with fork until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add chopped nuts, vanilla and small amounts of water until the mixture resembles fudge.
Form into balls or 1-inch rolls like "Tootsie Rolls."
Roll pieces of fudge mixture in your choice of ground peanuts or powdered or plain sugar or leave plain.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: baked dijon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 475 degrees.
Spray 13x9 inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Combine evaporated milk and mustard in shallow bowl.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese in separate shallow bowl.
Dip chicken into milk mixture, coating both sides, then into bread crumb mixture.
Place in prepared dish.

title: elegant banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, sour milk and bananas. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 325° oven for over 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean. I bake in large tube pan.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, sugar, salt, baking soda, flour and fruit cocktail.
Pour batter in baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out onto serving tray.

title: sausage balls #2
directions: Mix Bisquick, crumbled sausage and crumbled cheese. Mix well; roll into small balls. Cook on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook in iron skillet until thick.
Stir constantly.
Let cool before pouring into a baked pie shell filled with sliced strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: soft honey cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together.
Cream shortening and honey until fluffy.
Add egg and last add the honey.
Add buttermilk and fold in dry ingredients.
Put in 2 greased 8-inch layer pans or greased Bundt pan.
Put in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: egg nog(sugar-free, fat-free, cholesterol-free)
directions: Pour off 10 ounces of milk from half gallon and set aside.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 1 gallon container.
Stir in 10 ounces of milk that was set aside.
Refrigerate.
Shake or stir before serving.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Mix pudding and Tang to juice and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: crazy apple pie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, margarine and water.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into 9-inch pie pan.
Mix pie filling, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Pour into center of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 60 to 90 minutes.

title: cornetti
directions: Mix dry yeast and water; add sugar, salt, Crisco and flour. Mix well.
Place dough in bowl; let rest 15 minutes.
Knead well. Let rise about 45 minutes.
Knead again; shape.
Divide evenly into 12 balls.
Cut each ball in half.
With rolling pin or pasta machine roll each piece to 6 inches by 5 inches.
Roll the 5 inch side up in jelly roll fashion.
Take another ball and do the same. Put the two together and pinch center well.
Make sure one corner stands up.
Place the 6 cornetti on ungreased cookie sheets.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken with lime butter
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook until light brown, about 3 minutes per side.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter; keep warm.

title: mom's apricot pie
directions: Cook apricots 45 minutes to 1 hour until soft. Cover apricots with water to cook and add water as needed. Mash apricots; add pineapple and sugar. Thicken with 2 or 3 tablespoons cornstarch. Cook 10 minutes after adding pineapple and sugar. Filling will make enough for 2 pies. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sour cream pumpkin pie
directions: Mix white and brown sugar, flour and spices together.
Add sour cream, pumpkin and the egg yolks together.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the mixture.
Makes 2 pies. Bake in 300 degree oven 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carioca cooler
directions: Dissolve cocoa mix, coffee, sugar and cinnamon in hot water in a tall pitcher.
Stir in milk until blended.
Pour into 4 tall glasses.

title: mango salsa
directions: Combine mango, garlic, jalapeno pepper and parsley.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in glass mixing cup and microwave until sugar dissolves (approximately 2 minutes on High). Pour hot mixture over mango mixture.
Stir, cover and chill. Delicious with ham, pork or grilled chicken.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Put potatoes in.
Add sugar, water and vanilla.
Cover and cook about 40 minutes or until starts to candy.

title: muenster chicken
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Soak in eggs for 1 hour.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Saute in oil until chicken has browned.
Lay in a single layer in pan.
Pour chicken broth over chicken.
Lay sliced mushrooms across chicken.
Lay cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Put on broil at end to brown up the cheese.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix first four (4) ingredients. Chill.
When ready to serve, add cold ginger ale and sherbet.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for about 8 hours before forming in a ball and covering with chopped pecans or parsley.

title: mexican macaroli
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add meat, half at a time.
Stirring constantly, cook 5 to 7 minutes or until well browned.
Remove meat.
Add onion and garlic.
Stirring constantly, cook 1 minute or until crisp-tender.
Add beef broth, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Stir in meat, tomato sauce, chili powder, oregano, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes or until meat is tender and sauce is slightly thickened.

title: mavis' pear salad
directions: Drain
juice
from pears and add enough water to make 2 cups. Heat and pour over Jell-O.	Mash pears and combine with cream cheese.
Add
to
jello.
Add Cool Whip to pears, cream cheese and jello.
Refrigerate.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Mix together and pour into greased and floured 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick is clean.
Cut and serve with warm sauce.

title: jenny's french bread
directions: Slice bread lengthwise.
Mix rest of the ingredients and spread over both halves of bread.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Mix ingredients according to the order listed.
Be sure to add the boiled eggs and raw oysters last.
Pour this mixture into a hot, greased baking dish.
Bake at 250° for approximately 40 to 50 minutes, or until set and golden brown.

title: strawberry cheese delight
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Beat cream cheese and butter, softened.
Add sugar and blend.
Pour over angel food cake.
Mash strawberries and pour glaze over them.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over cake. Serve.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Mix butter, sugar and chopped nuts in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, boil and stir for about 5 minutes.
Put a layer of graham crackers on a bread pan.
Spoon mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: poor man's pie(spanish tortilla)
directions: Saute onion and potatoes in olive oil in omelette pan or 10-inch frying pan.
Cover with lid and cook about 25 minutes.
Use the same number of eggs as potatoes.
Blend eggs and pour over vegetables.
Cook until solid.
Flip and cook other side until nicely browned, about 10 minutes on each side.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Arrange carrots in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 4 to 8 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.
Remove from steamer and keep warm.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add honey and lemon juice, stirring until smooth.
Add carrots, tossing gently.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and shortening in a bowl; add egg yolks, one at a time and blend after each.
Add flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together with the milk.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff and carefully fold into mixture.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven (preheated) for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Be sure that cake is firm.
If cake is properly brown, it will have a delicate crunchy crust.
It will be better after several days but is delicious soon as it is cool.
Vanilla is not recommended for this cake but you can use either lemon, orange or nutmeg as flavoring.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar together; add eggs.
Put cream of tartar and soda in milk; add to oleo, sugar and egg mixture.
Mix flour with all ingredients and add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Mix (beat) mayonnaise and cheese together; add artichokes. Place in greased baking dish and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: jiffy potato casserole
directions: Combine soups, milk and sour cream.
Mix until smooth.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with cheese during the last 15 or 20 minutes.

title: cool refresher
directions: Mix fruit juices together; chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and stir.
Pour over ice cubes with cherries in centers.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt and then beat together the buttermilk, cereal, soda, eggs and oil.
Refrigerate.
To cook, fill greased (or Pam-sprayed) muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Mix will keep in refrigerator for six weeks.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken.
Mix well.
Reduce heat to low.
Add chicken; stir and cook until bubbly (about 10 minutes).

title: "big hit" cheese snacks
directions: Beat together mustard, Worcestershire, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Split chilies and arrange in bottom of pan. Cover with grated cheese and egg mixture. Sprinkle with paprika. Cook for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cut in squares and serve immediately.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well and pour into large iron skillet which has been heated and well-greased.
Bake at 375° until done.
Serve while hot.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese, half and half and butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese mixture is soft and creamy and butter is melted.
Blend in frosting mix and stir to blend well.
Add peppermint extract and food coloring of your choice.
You may divide the batch to make 2 or 3 colors.
Roll mixture into balls or drop by teaspoon on waxed paper lined cookie sheet; press with fork.
Let stand at room temperature until firm and dry.

title: hamburger pepper steak
directions: Shape meat into 6 oval steaks.
Brown lightly in a large skillet. Top steaks with green peppers. Cover.
Cook over medium heat for about 8 to 10 minutes or to desired doneness and peppers are still crisp. Makes 6 servings.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Thoroughly mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs and stir until well mixed.
Add the grated apple and walnuts (if you like walnuts!).
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan in a 325° oven for approximately an hour.
Test cake for "doneness" by putting a butter knife into the middle.
It will come out clean if the cake is done.

title: bar cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Mix all of other ingredients and add to melted cheese.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into jar or other container.
Cool, then cover.
Refrigerate.
(Best if stands at least one day before using to develop flavor and smoothness.)

title: cucumber delight
directions: Score cucumber with tines of fork.
Slice paper thin.
Put in shallow dish and sprinkle salt over.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend well the first 3 ingredients and pack in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: tatios yny popty(potatoes in the oven; welsh)
directions: Take potatoes, peel and quarter.
Place in bottom of roasting pan. Slice onion over potatoes.
Pepper and salt to taste.
Place chunk of pork on top of potatoes.
Pour boiling water over meat until water covers potatoes.
Roast meat and potatoes until done. Bake at 325°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard cook desired number of eggs.
When done, plunge into ice water and remove shells.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolks to a bowl.
Arrange white halves on a platter.
Press yolks through a sieve or mash thoroughly.
Add enough mayonnaise and a little mustard or Dijonnaise to make creamy enough to fill the egg white shells.
You can add white pepper and salt if desired.
Fill the white shells.
Garnish with a dusting of paprika, parsley sprigs and radish roses.
Cover and chill immediately.
Do not leave at room temperature.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and
boil squash and onion; drain and add other ingredients, except butter and dressing mix.
Mix well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Roll into small balls and flatten with a fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: beef and broccoli pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain well. Stir in flour, salt and garlic salt.

Add milk and cream cheese. Cook and stir until smooth and bubbly. Add a small amount of this mixture to the beaten egg; return this to the beef mixture. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in cooked broccoli.
Pour into pie shell.
Slice cheese and arrange atop the mixture. Cover with second pie shell and seal edges.
Make slits in top.
Brush with a little milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Prepare wafer crumbs in blender.
Combine with coconut, 1 cup sugar, corn
syrup
and rum in bowl.
Mix well and shape into small balls
3/4-inch
diameter.
Sift remaining sugar on waxed paper.
Roll balls in sugar.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a cake pan.
Pour the coconut and nuts in the bottom of the pan.
Mix the cake according to package directions and pour into the pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour on top of the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: judge's choice german-chocolate ice cream
directions: In mixer bowl, beat eggs until light.
Add sugar. Beat until well combined.
Add cream, chocolate, vanilla and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Beat well. Stir in milk, pecans and coconut.

title: yum yum macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
In saucepan, melt oleo.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook slowly for a few minutes.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Mix well.

title: scandinavian cucumbers
directions: Stir together sour cream, parsley, tarragon, sugar and chives. Gently fold in cucumbers.
Cover and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, sugar and gelatin. Mix well. Add half and half, lemon juice and extracts. Beat until smooth. Fold in the whipped cream. Stir in enough milk to measure 1 gallon. Add food coloring, if desired. Freeze in batches according to manufacturer's directions. Refrigerate extra mixture until it can be frozen. Allow to ripen in ice cream freezer or firm up in refrigerator freezer for 2 to 4 hours before serving. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving. Yield: 1 gallon.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream sauce
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken.
Finely chop dried beef and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange bacon wrapped chicken on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in a 250° to 275° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: ela's glaze for graham crackers
directions: Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
After boiling 2 minutes, spread on crackers, which have been broken apart and put on cookie sheet.
Spread fast for it will harden quickly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In 2-quart utility dish, combine margarine, onion and celery. Place in Radarange oven for 4 minutes on Roast.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Stuffs 4 to 6 pound bird.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend for 30 seconds.
Pour into greased pie pan (10-inch).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Makes its own crust.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix and pat oleo and flour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix and spread on cooled baked crust Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix together pudding and milk. Spread over the mixture and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: nectar cake
directions: Combine.
Cook in Bundt cake pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Cook spaghetti in chicken stock.
Lightly grease casserole.
Put half the spaghetti in the bottom, then a layer of half the chopped chicken, onion and pepper mixture.
Mix the two undiluted soups in medium bowl with 1 cup chicken broth.
Pour half over spaghetti. Add a layer of cheese.
Then repeat layers in same order with remaining ingredients, topping with cheese and "wetting down" with a few spoons of stock.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
More cheese can be used, if desired.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 18 muffin tins.
Beat margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add bananas, milk, vanilla and eggs. Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix until moist.
Add the chocolate chips and walnuts.
Fill tins 2/3 full. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot ham on buns
directions: Combine onion, mustard, poppy seed and butter.
Spread mixture on bun like butter, then put slice of cheese on bun on top with a slice of ham.
Wrap each bun individually in foil and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
You may also leave unwrapped and bake at 250° until done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Remove stems and set caps aside. Finely chop stems and cook with garlic and basil in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Brush mushroom caps with remaining butter and place in baking dish.
Spoon filling into mushroom caps.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Remove kernels from corn.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, eggs, milk and corn.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Heat oil (1-inch deep) to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry a few at a time until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Makes approximately 36 fritters.

title: sand tarts
directions: Separate whites and yolks of 2 eggs and set aside.
(Use yolks for other recipes.)
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Combine all ingredients.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook noodles.
Mix together and spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain off fat.
Add vegetables.
Saute until tender.
While sausage and vegetables are cooking, add soup to 4 cups of water.
Heat to boil.
Add rice and cook until done. Combine with sausage mixture and add half of the almonds.
Pour into casserole dish and top with remainder of almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cholesterol-free banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl mix first 7 ingredients with pastry blender, cut in corn oil spread until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in bananas, apple juice, egg substitute, walnuts and vanilla just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center of bread comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool slightly.
Serve warm or cool completely.
Makes 18 servings.

title: crazy crust fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 stick margarine in a Pyrex pie pan (10 1/2 x 11-inch).
Mix the listed ingredients thoroughly and pour into the pie pan.
Add can of fruit and juice (peaches, apple, cherry and blueberry).
Bake until done, about 1 hour. Fresh fruit can be used instead of canned ones.

title: barbecued beef short ribs
directions: Rub ribs well with bottled sauce for gravy.
In hot fat, in Dutch oven, brown ribs well, about 15 minutes.
Add garlic, onion and celery.
Stir in cornstarch, tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper, allspice, mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer, covered, turning occasionally, 1 1/2 hours or until ribs are fork-tender. Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Toss with caraway seed, if desired.
Serve ribs, sliced on noodles, pass gravy separately.

title: martha hapner's oatmeal pie
directions: Mix.
Fill unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat until smooth and foamy.
Add buttermilk, coconut, melted butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Make your own chili recipe without beans.
Need enough to fill a Dutch oven about 3/4ths full.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl. Add salad oil, water and pumpkin. Blend well, then add flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and baking soda.
Mix well. Pour into ungreased loaf pans (2 or 3 loaves).
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Blend together butter, sugars, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Blend together both mixtures.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breast and tear in strips or small pieces. Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour on top of chicken.
Add poppy seed and butter to crushed crackers.
Sprinkle on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms.
Line the bottom of pan with this. Mix souffle with egg and put in pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until it puffs up.

title: hot chocolate
directions: In a medium saucepan combine chocolate, sugar and 1/2 c milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Stir in remaining milk, heat through.
DO NOT BOIL!
Add whipped cream and marshmallows.

title: barbecue franks and rice
directions: Split hot dogs down the middle and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. In medium skillet, melt butter and add onion, chili powder and hot dogs; brown.
Add tomato soup and water; bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer to thicken.
Pour over prepared rice to serve.

title: pasta salad dressing
directions: Prepare in blender.
Better if made ahead of time.

title: quick, delicious potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for one hour. Can be microwaved.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Using a food processor or mixer, beat the butter until it is light and fluffy.
Beat in lemon juice and powdered sugar. Mash the fruit and beat it into the butter a spoonful at a time until well blended.
It is important to add berries slowly so it will be absorbed evenly.
Mound butter into small bowl and serve with bread.

title: apple pie
directions: Arrange apple slices in one crust.
Sprinkle tapioca, Equal and a little cinnamon over apples.
Place second pie crust over pie.
Crimp edges, moisten with water, if necessary.
Bake at 400° or until apples are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies(makes 12 dozen)
directions: Cream margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add the flavorings and vinegar. Beat thoroughly.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix into butter in this order:
Sugar, eggs, flour, nuts, chocolate chips, vanilla and bourbon.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add with hot water.
Mix. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage; press crescent rolls in a 12-inch pizza pan to form crust.
Spoon sausage onto crust.
Sprinkle on frozen hash brown.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lime pickles
directions: Don't peel cucumbers.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Soak 24 hours in 2 gallons of water and lime.
Wash thoroughly and let stand 3 hours in cold water.
Drain and let stand overnight in mixture of remaining ingredients.
I heat it to boiling before adding to cuke slices, which I have in a plastic pail, if a large amount. In the morning, boil 35 minutes and seal.
I add some alum if pickles are too soft, while cooking.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Cut shortening into the dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add dissolved yeast to buttermilk.
Mix yeast and buttermilk mixture with flour mixture.
Place in airtight container and chill for at least 20 minutes before rolling out. Cut biscuits.
Place on baking sheet and allow them to sit in a warm place 10 minutes before baking.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: blender whole wheat pancakes
directions: Pour the milk and wheat in a blender.
Liquify for 4 minutes. While still running, add the eggs, sugar, salt, melted butter and baking soda.
Add baking powder last and stop blender as soon as thoroughly mixed.
Bake on hot griddle and serve.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and slightly beaten eggs.
Add melted butter.
Add the dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, mini muffins for 15 minutes.

title: turkish mints(the stuff of many a childhood story and dream.)
directions: Soak gelatin in water 20 minutes.
Put sugar and water in saucepan and bring to boiling.
Add gelatin and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into shallow pan to one-inch in thickness; cool.
Remove to board, cut in cubes and roll in powdered sugar.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except vinegar and simmer for 45 minutes. Add vinegar and cook to desired consistency. Put in sterilized jars and put in boiling water for 15 minutes.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: mustard biscuits
directions: Bake biscuits according to can directions; let cool.
Split and layer with shaved ham and Swiss cheese.
Place in baking dish. Melt margarine and mix with mustard and onions.
Spoon this mixture over each biscuit and cover.
Refrigerate overnight. Reheat slowly in oven for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Take butter out of refrigerator; set aside room temperature. Open coconut.
Take out pulp (do not take skin off).
Wash and grate.
Measure 3 cups grated coconut and add rest of ingredients. Grease pan and sprinkle with flour (cookie sheet).
Shape ingredients into little balls and place on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place balls in oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes about 33 pieces.

title: asian beef noodles
directions: Stack beef steaks; cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
In medium bowl combine beef, jalapeno pepper and oil.
Toss to coat.
Break noodles into 4 pieces; reserve seasoning packet.
Cook noodles as package directs; drain.
Heat large nonstick skillet over medium high heat until hot.
Stir-fry beef (1/2 at a time) 1 minute or until no longer pink.
Do not overcook.
Remove beef; keep warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
In blender mix zucchini, oil and eggs.
Add zucchini.
Mix to dry milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix.
Divide equally and put in two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: everlasting cabbage slaw
directions: Shred and chop cabbage, onion and pepper; mix together.
Boil together all other ingredients until well blended.
Pour over slaw and let set several hours.
Store in refrigerator.
Lasts and lasts.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: In large bowl blend sugar, margarine and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add gradually to chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls into confectioners sugar, coating lightly.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased baking sheets, 2 inches apart, flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan onto wire rack to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: plain roll dough
directions: Soften yeast in warm water. Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm and add softened yeast and eggs. Gradually stir in flour to form soft dough. Beat vigorously; cover and let rise to double in bulk. Turn out onto lightly floured board and use as desired. Grease pans if used for cinnamon rolls. Bake in 350° oven. Makes about 3 loaf pans full.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Measure margarine and sugar into large mixing bowl; beat until well blended and smooth. Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix until well combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies cereal, semi-sweet chocolate morsels and raisins.
Drop by level measuring tablespoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, and chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
This makes a lot and freezes well.

title: country breakfast
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in the margarine in a large skillet on medium until tender.
Beat eggs, milk, ham or bacon, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and onion in skillet.
When egg begins to set, gently lift up around edges to allow raw egg to run under and cook.
Cook until done.

title: chicken rivel soup
directions: Cook chicken with water, salt and onion until tender.
Remove chicken.
Add celery and carrots to broth.
Cook until tender. Take chicken off bones and place in broth with carrots and celery. Add rivels to boiling broth; a small handful at a time, stirring constantly to avoid big lumps of dough.
If too thick, add more water to desired consistency.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in small amount of corn oil.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup, enchilada sauce, milk and green chiles. Simmer while assembling enchiladas.
Dip tortilla in hot corn oil to soften.
Fill center of tortilla with shredded cheese and black olives.
Fold edges over filling to form enchiladas.
Brushing with a small amount of enchilada sauce helps to keep tortilla soft and closed.
Place enchiladas into the skillet of sauce and continue to simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Cover with remainder of shredded cheese before serving.
Can also be prepared in oven.
I personally prefer them prepared in the oven.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Wash and dry beef. Place in a deep container and cover with buttermilk and lemon juice. Marinate in refrigerator for 2 days, turning several times. Remove; wash off buttermilk. Place beef in pot or kettle.

Add wine, water, salt, bay leaf, peppercorns and vinegar. Cook, covered, for about 3 hours or until very tender. Remove beef. Strain stock, reserving liquid. Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour. Stir in stock slowly; simmer until slightly thickened. Add gingersnaps and currants; cook until sauce is thickened. Add sugar to taste.

title: sour cream swiss steak
directions: Dredge steak on both sides with flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Heat oil in skillet; brown steak on both sides. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese; cover skillet. Simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender; sprinkle Swiss cheese on steak while still hot.

title: cream cheese bread
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar,
butter
and salt.
Mix well and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve
yeast	in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in sour
cream	mixture
and eggs.
Stir in flour gradually.	Dough will
be	soft.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix them all together and then add 2 cups peanut butter.
Mix all that together and then roll little meatball size balls into sesame seed or coconut.
Then put them into the refrigerator.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine
sugar, flour and salt.
Add all other ingredients, except coconut.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened,
about
15 minutes.
Add half of the coconut; mix and pour
into
the baked pie shell.
Beat the egg whites with 1 teaspoon
vanilla and 3 tablespoons sugar until stiff. Spread on top
of
pie and sprinkle with rest of the coconut. Bake at
350° for
to 15 minutes and meringue is browned. Refrigerate until completely cooled before cutting.

title: roasted new potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine potatoes, garlic, oil, salt, pepper, thyme and rosemary in medium bowl. Toss to coat evenly. Place potatoes in single layer on 16-inch sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Fold over potatoes and crimp edges to seal.
Bake on cookie sheet 1 hour until tender.
Open foil and sprinkle on parsley.

title: electric skillet dinner
directions: Cut round steak in small pieces and brown in bacon drippings. Add tomatoes, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover with gravy.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo and toss with stuffing mix.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl; add half of stuffing mix and pour in greased casserole.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Freezes nicely.
Good for your next buffet.

title: oreo cake
directions: Cream oleo, cheese and sugar.
In another bowl, mix milk, pudding and add Cool Whip.
Combine mix.
Put 1/3 cookies in deep glass bowl.
Then layer 1/2 pudding, 1/3 cookies, rest of pudding. Top with rest of cookies.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ambrosia
directions: Whip the whipping cream until stiff; fold in sour cream.
Add drained fruit and all other ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: lasagne - short cut style
directions: Brown meat.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water. Drain and rinse.
Place 1/3 noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1/3 sauce; add 1/3 Mozzarella and 1/3 cottage cheese.
Repeat layers twice and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes to cool and set.
Cut in squares.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice carrots and cook.
Simmer sliced onion in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle crushed cracker crumbs on top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas and vanilla. Sift and add dry ingredients.
Mix. Add nuts.
Spread in 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake.
Best if frosted with a white icing.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and Karo until ball forms.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla, butter or margarine and peanut butter.
Beat and pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool.

title: what's it casserole
directions: Brown ground turkey, salt and pepper to taste.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer meat, onions and peas.
Pour soup on top.
Add cheese, then Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: ten minute meal
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan; drain.
Mix in creamed corn and stewed tomatoes.
Heat and serve with corn bread or crackers. Makes 4 servings.

title: santa fe dip
directions: Cook beef, sausage and onion until done; drain.
Chop cheese into meat and cook on low.
Add Ro-Tel while cheese is melting.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Start cake in cold oven. Cream the butter, sugar and cream cheese until fluffy. Add one egg at a time and beat while adding. Add vanilla and flour, sifted 3 times.
Beat until blended and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until done at 325°.

title: ayame's cake and frosting
directions: Mix these ingredients together, then fold in egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar, beating until they peak.
Bake cake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Line your cake pan with waxed paper before baking for easy, clean turning.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream together grated cheese and flour.
Add spices.
May have to use hands.
Put through cookie press.
Bake at 325° about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: pepperoni en croute
directions: Unroll 8 ounce package crescent rolls into one piece.
Slice pepperoni thin.
Dip pepperoni in egg yolk and little flour. Place pepperoni in rolled out crescent roll.
Roll up and seal. Brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until browned.
Slice in bite size pieces.
Serve with mustards.

title: twinkling rolls
directions: Scald milk, then set aside to cool to a lukewarm temperature. Sprinkle yeast in lukewarm water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to dissolve.

title: hawaiian gems
directions: Heat sugar and ice cream topping to a boil.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in cream cheese.
Continue stirring until cream cheese is melted. Add coconut flavoring.
Mix well.
Stir in crumbs, pecans, and coconut.
Roll into small balls, about 1 inch in diameter. Roll the balls in coconut.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 to 6 1/2 doz.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in unsalted water.
Drain.
In a bowl mix 2 soups with milk.
Add tuna.
Mix in noodles and pour in casserole dish. Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: hershey's old-fashion chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: new york cheesecake(low carb, no sugar)
directions: With electric mixer, beat cream cheese and Equal until fluffy. Beat in eggs, cornstarch, sour cream and vanilla until well blended.

Pour into in a 9-inch spring-form or flat glass pan. Place cheese cake pan into a roasting pan with 1-inch of hot water. Bake at 300° until set in center, approximately 45 to 60 minutes. Turn oven off and let cheesecake cool 3 hours in the oven with the door ajar.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
In a saucepan, mix broth and peas. Add cream of mushroom soup, milk and onion.
Cook until bubbly. In large bowl, mix Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix and margarine. Place half dressing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Spoon all of chicken mixture over this.
Top with remaining dressing.
Place in oven and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until it is brown.

title: cream of mushroom delight
directions: Place soup, milk, flour and drained mushrooms in large soup pot, stirring frequently, over medium heat, until mixture begins to boil.

title: ham-n-cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: abe lincoln pie
directions: Cook until thickened (coats spoon).
Dissolve 1 package Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to hot custard.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool thoroughly.
Add 2 egg whites, well beaten (no sugar added).
Beat 1 pint whipping cream and fold in whipped cream.
Grate sweetened chocolate over top.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies in graham cracker or chocolate crumb crust.
Can be frozen for a short period.

title: western beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or put in crock-pot for several hours. Stir occasionally.

title: dip
directions: Blend dehydrated onion soup mix with sour cream.
Chill. Yield:
2 cups.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 1 g, fat 6 g, calories per serving 66.
Two tablespoons = 1 fat exchange.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package, but not until soft.
Drain and mix with celery, onion, mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into baking dish and cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain cans and combine all vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients together; mix with vegetables.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: jodi's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Melt cheese with soups in saucepan. Mix all together.
Saute 1 stick of butter with 1 sleeve Ritz crackers and top casserole.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chile relleno torta
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix grated cheeses and spread evenly in buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs; add flour slowly and then beat in half and half.
If mixture is lumpy, strain it.
Pour egg mixture over cheeses in pie plate.
Carefully spoon chiles over the surface, then spoon picante sauce over all.
Bake about 45 minutes or until center is set.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine cream soups with taco sauce and milk.
Dip tortillas in mixture and line bottom of 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Add half of the chicken, chili and cheese, forming a layer.
Repeat tortilla layer, ending with cheese.
Sprinkle olives over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend peanut butter and butter well.
Add sugar until creamy. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Freeze firm.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate using toothpicks and let sit on wax paper a few minutes.
Keep most frozen as you are dipping.
Only take a few out at a time.
They dip better if frozen.
Serves lots.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers and butter. Place in 9 x 13 pan. Crush crackers and mix with melted butter. Spread over mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix well first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, blending well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(I put my chocolate chips and nuts in batter before baking.)

title: philadelphia cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, softened cream cheese, brown and white sugars and egg; add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in chips and nuts.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
You can ice these with your favorite icing.

title: sante fe stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, blend onion soup mix, oil, water, lime juice and garlic powder; let stand 5 minutes.
Bring soup mixture to a boil.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Cook uncovered 5 minutes, stirring frequently until chicken is done.
Serve over rice. Makes about 4 servings.

title: dalmation steak burgers
directions: Mix onion soup mix with 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Combine ground beef, onion soup mix and pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Make into steak size patties.

title: date salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Gradually add pineapple juice and sugar to softened cream cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Add pineapple, pecans and dates.
Mix well.
Whip the cream using chilled bowl and beaters.
Fold whipped cream into date mixture.
Spoon into serving dish and chill.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. (Put mix in 3 layer pans.) For moister cake, put pineapple juice on layers after cooking.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Roll chicken pieces into the first 2 ingredients.
Place in melted butter dish.
Pour the remaining ingredients over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, pecans and sugar in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pour the melted butter over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding, milk, Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Layer bananas, cookies and mixture.
Cool in icebox several hours before serving.

title: taco fiesta chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 13 x 9 baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. In large bowl, combine tomatoes and taco sauce. Mix well. Stir in chicken. In medium bowl, combine refried beans and sour cream; mix well. Spread about 1 cup chicken mixture in bottom of dish. Top with taco shells. Spread with half bean

mixture and half chicken mixture. Sprinkle with cheese, onion and olives. Layer 1 to 2 more times. Cheese on top with some more green onion. Bake, covered with foil for 50 minutes. Uncover and bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Garnish with cheese, onion and sour cream.

title: chewy squares
directions: *I use butterscotch chips, Heath bar chips or chocolate chips, half a bag of whichever.
If I use these, I cut the nuts down to half.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all and chill.
Serve with crackers, chips or on bread as a sandwich.

title: scalloped eggplant(tastes like scalloped oysters)
directions: Cut eggplant into 1 inch cubes; soak 1 hour in salted water. Drain and mush with potato masher.
Combine eggs, milk, margarine and pepper; add to "mushed" eggplant.
In a greased casserole, place a layer of eggplant, a layer of crumbled crackers, a layer of eggplant, layer of crackers, etc, ending with crackers on top. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
May add 1 small can of mushrooms or soup; if desired.

title: peanut butter-cocoa bit cookies
directions: Cream the white sugar, brown sugar, butter or oleo, well-beaten eggs, peanut butter and vanilla together.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in cocoa bits; form dough into balls the size of large walnuts.
Crisscross with fork.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: lemon delight
directions: Spread in a large Pyrex dish or a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen yogurt floats
directions: Scoop frozen yogurt into 12 tall glasses.
Fill with club soda.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: russian cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into glass dish.
Chill overnight.

title: danish squares
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening as pie crust.
Scald milk and cool.
Add yeast and dissolve thoroughly.
Add eggs and combine two mixtures and let stand 2 hours.
Roll out on sugared board and cut into 3-inch squares.
Spread with pineapple preserves or apricot preserves and fold over corners to seal.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: slumgullion
directions: Saute garlic and onion in butter.
Add ground beef and brown. Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and pork and beans.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for at least 30 minutes.
This can be made earlier in the day and reheated.
Great with cornbread.

title: soy sauce and sesame seed chicken
directions: Spray a flat pan with nonstick spray.
Add chicken and cover pan with soy sauce (it needs plenty of sauce).
Shake sesame seed over; cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Uncover; baste.
Turn oven down to 350°; cook about 30 minutes or until well done.
It will stay hot a long time and seems to be a favorite every time.

title: texas walnut pie
directions: In saucepan, slowly melt butter.
Add cocoa; blend until smooth.
Stir hot water into cocoa mixture and blend.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar and salt with a wire whisk until well blended.
Stir cocoa mixture into the dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg and blend until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust (prebake 5 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting into thin slices.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chocolate stars
directions: Cream sugar, butter or butter Crisco, egg, milk and vanilla. Add baking cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and flour.
After all mixed, cover and chill.
Divide dough into 3rds.
Doing one at a time, roll out thin.
Cut out stars.
Every other tray, I cut out small circle in middle of cookie.
When all cool, I put lemon icing or pink peppermint on one side of cookie.
Place cut out cookie on top.
Looks and tastes good.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on ungreased pan.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and soda together.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and the remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour and vanilla; blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, peanut butter chips or nuts. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked artichoke hearts
directions: Combine all ingredients except paprika.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: cowboy slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and green pepper.
Mix other ingredients; pour over cabbage.
Toss to blend.
Chill.

title: cinnamon applesauce delight
directions: Bring the cup of water to boil; add Imperials and stir until completely dissolved.
Reheat to boiling point and add jello.
Add applesauce and pour into desired mold.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, add onion, bell pepper, garlic, salt, chili powder and simmer 15 minutes.
Add ground beef and cook until tender.
Add beans, tomatoes, corn, potatoes and water. Cook 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower and onion.
Brown bacon; crumble and add to cauliflower and onion.
Mix Parmesan cheese, sugar and mayonnaise. Mix well and chill.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Cream the shortening.
Add sugar slowly and cream until fluffy.
Stir in well beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Place 1 cup shortening in a deep fryer.
Heat until 1-inch bread cube will brown when dropped in.
Turn dough out on a floured board.
Roll out a small amount at a time.
Cut with a doughnut cutter and drop in hot shortening.
Let brown and remove immediately.
Keep shortening hot enough so the doughnuts will not soak it up.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 2/3 stick margarine and stir in graham cracker crumbs; press into a 9 x 13 pan.
In a small bowl, beat sugar, eggs and rest of margarine for 15 minutes; spread over top of graham cracker then place sliced bananas on that, then the pineapple and cool whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherry halves.
Serve chilled.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy cherry brunch ring
directions: Heat
oven
Lightly grease 12-cup fluted tube baking pan.
Place
brown
sugar, cherry halves, nuts and 1/4 cup melted
butter
in bottom of pan.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
In
small
bowl combine sugar, cinnamon and pumpkin pie spice.
Dip one side of each biscuit in remaining butter, then into cinnamon sugar mixture.
Place 10 biscuits, coating side down, in prepared pan, overlapping slightly.
Repeat with remaining 10 biscuits
for
second
layer.
Bake
for 40 to 50 minutes or until
golden.
Cool 2 minutes; invert onto serving plate.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Cut 1/2 of the stems into tiny pieces.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Stuff mushroom caps. Broil 5 to 8 minutes.

title: tex-mex soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Add 3 to 4 cups water as desired for thickness.
Cover; cook over low heat about 1 hour.

title: olive nut spread
directions: In large bowl combine:

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into 3 sections; throw away small pointed tips.
Rinse and pat dry.
Pour milk in a large bowl, and put flour in a separate bowl.
Dip wings in the milk, then in the flour to fully coat.
As oil heats, melt 1/2 stick of butter, then set aside to cool.
Fry chicken wings until crispy, about 10 to 12 minutes, they should stop making crackling noise in oil.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Combine all 3 ingredients.
Mix slowly at first, then increase speed until all lumps are gone and the ingredients are mixed well. Spread on toast from the toaster.
May refrigerate or keep at room temperature.
(It is easier to spread at room temperature.) Children love this and it is something they can fix.

title: pizza
directions: Saute hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
Add mushrooms, tomato juice and seasoning and cook until consistency to spread.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine first six ingredients, mixing well; set aside. Beat orange juice, eggs, oil and orange peel until thoroughly mixed.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Makes 12 servings.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jello according to package directions.
Add other ingredients and allow to set.

title: chili chicken
directions: In a large bowl, mix the chicken with half of the tomato puree,
ginger-garlic paste, 2 Tbsp. soy sauce, vinegar, 2 Tbsp. green chili sauce, cayenne and salt.
Marinate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: janice's spaghetti
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Cool.
Add meat to bacon grease.
Cook until all red is gone.
Crumble bacon and add.
Add garlic powder, onion powder, black pepper and sugar.
Add tomato juice; bring back to boil.
Simmer while you cook spaghetti in boiling salted water only until tender.
Rinse spaghetti in hot water.
Put spaghetti in bowls; top with sauce.

title: tapioca salad
directions: Drain liquid from all cans; save and add water to make 3 cups of liquid.
Boil juice and tapioca to thicken, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and canned fruits or other fruits may be added.
Also easy to cut in half.

title: fudge cake brownies
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate and margarine.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and gradually add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with greased foil and pour mix in.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: new england seafood feast
directions: Thaw the condensed shrimp soup.
Mix the melted margarine into the soup.
Layer the fish in a buttered casserole.
Pour the shrimp soup (undiluted) over fish; spread bread crumbs over top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar with apples.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Beat eggs and add oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add to eggs.
Add chocolate chips, then apples.
Bake for 40 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pan cookie
directions: Blend all ingredients together. Spread dough into pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken-potato casserole
directions: Spray baking pan with Pam and layer chicken parts which have been seasoned with lite seasoning and garlic powder in pan.
Broil for 5 or 10 minutes.
Layer potatoes and onions on chicken.
Mix broth, milk and flour and pour over chicken and potato mix. Cover; bake for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Sprinkle cheese on top and brown.

title: holiday roast
directions: Bake at 300° for 6 to 8 hours.

title: quick sand(apple dip)
directions: Core apples and slice thinly.
Store in Ziploc bags with lemon and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip, together in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Let cool completely.
Fold in Cool Whip.
For a stronger flavor, use a medium container of Cool Whip.

title: pepperoni pizza casserole(microwave)
directions: Combine ground beef, green peppers and onions in 2-quart casserole.
Cook covered on full power for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through and drain. Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cook covered on full power for 6 1/2 to 9 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil; stir.
Continue cooking on medium power for 8 to 12 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Top with cheese.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil and dressing.
Mix well.
Put crackers in large bowl. Pour oil mixture over crackers.
Mix well.
Let stand.
Mix well again.
Keep in covered container.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon out into greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: spanish hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, green pepper and celery and then add tomato sauce, ketchup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt bars in microwave except one of them.
Mix in Cool Whip. Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Spread thin layer of Cool Whip on top of pie.
Shave or grate the other bar on top of the pie. Chill for 3 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil in a large pot.
Add potatoes, celery and onions. Cook until potatoes are tender. Add butter and milk.
Bring to a simmer and add salt and pepper to taste.
In a small bowl, stir beaten egg into the flour.
Stir until a grainy mixture. Sprinkle small amounts at a time into the soup and continue stirring.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry orange with cherry gelatin
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry with orange and pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and pour in preheated oiled skillet.
Bak at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: squash and onions
directions: Place in a skillet and cook until liquid is cooked out and onion is tender.

title: holiday delight(diet)
directions: Combine and mix well the flour, butter and chopped nuts.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, Equal and Cool Whip together.
Spread on cooked crust.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups whipping cream.
Mix chocolate pudding with 1 1/2 cups whipping cream.

When puddings have set, you can either mix together and spread on top of cheese layer or you can add one at a time and layer them (either vanilla first, then chocolate or chocolate first, then vanilla).
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip, if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, vanilla, baking powder, coconut, and pineapple with half of juice. Pour into 2 unbaked shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: louise's cookies
directions: Mix together and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Grease cookie sheets and make
into small balls.
Cook in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Blend ingredients.
Roll in ball; flatten with glass or spoon.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix eggs, milk and salt.
Add 1/2 teaspoon dry mustard.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Add mushrooms, onions and peppers, if desired.
Bake at 350° until egg mixture is set.

title: rice and green chilies
directions: Mix all together and heat in oven until done.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Melt butter in 5 1/2-quart Dutch oven; add flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir mixture continually until very dark brown, but not scorched.
Add onions, celery, green pepper, okra and tomatoes.
Blend all ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp and crabmeat.
Stir thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat for 25 minutes.
Add shrimp and crabmeat.
Cook for 20 minutes more.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: hot milk cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs until thick, about 5 minutes on high speed.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to batter with vanilla and beat at low speed until smooth.
In saucepan, heat milk and butter, just until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Add to batter, beating until combined.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then add Marshmallow Creme and beat until smooth with electric mixer.
Makes approximately 25 servings.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt; blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips and set aside.
Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Combine water, salad oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and liquids, beat well.
Pour into paper-lined muffin pans, filling 1/2 full.
Top with heaping teaspoonful of cheese mixture.
Bake for 25 to 28 minutes at 350°.

title: white trash
directions: Mix cereal, raisins and nuts in large bowl.
Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips.
Pour over cereal mixture and stir until coated.
Pour sugar in trash bag.
Pour cereal mixture into sugar and shake until well coated.
Pour into covered container.

title: cherry breeze
directions: Mix together crumbs and butter and press firmly on bottom and sides to make crust.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add Eagle milk, blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Refrigerate 3-4 hours till firm.
DO NOT FREEZE!!!.
Top with chilled pie filling.

title: heavenly cream(no-fat whipped cream)
directions: Pour milk into small stainless steel or copper bowl.
Set it in the freezer until ice crystals just begin to form, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Use a hand-held electric mixer and thicken the mixture by beating in dry milk. Continue to beat on high until soft peaks form, about 2 minutes.
If you'd like the cream sweetened, pour in 1 tablespoon light honey and beat until stiff peaks form, about 2 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken about 45 minutes, then cut up.
Cook spaghetti. Chop up the onion, celery, black olives and green olives.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Combine with chicken and spaghetti.
Bake in large 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Blend in other ingredients.
Bake in 1 pound coffee cans for nice size loaves or bake in loaf pans at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken
into desired chunks-add water with salt and pepper to taste and cook till chicken is fork tender.
Chop vegetables-add to chicken.
Cook till veggies are tender.
Add milk and butter.
Mix flour or corn starch with a little water-pour into chicken mix and stir-add more thickening if a heavy stew is wanted.

title: family reunion chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts (2 whole) until done, debone, save 1/4 cup broth.
Melt stick of margarine and crumble l stack of crackers into it; stir.
In 13 x 9 Pyrex dish, layer 1/2 cracker mixture. Break chicken into bite-size pieces and put on top.
Mix sour cream, soup, and chicken broth together and spread on top of chicken.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: tammy's spaghetti
directions: In a large saucepan, cover spaghetti with water.
Add a few drops of oil to prevent noodles from sticking together.
Cook until spaghetti is done.
In another saucepan, crumble and brown hamburger meat.
Season with 1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce and other seasonings.
When meat is browned, drain off grease.
You may rinse to reduce fat.
Combine drained hamburger, tomato sauce, remaining Worcestershire sauce and additional seasonings and simmer until spaghetti is done.
Drain spaghetti and mix with sauce.
Simmer together for at least 20 minutes.
If too dry, add a little more water.
If too soupy, cook a little longer.
Great with garlic bread and salad.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Reserve drippings.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in drippings until done.
Combine sausage, sauteed vegetables, long grain and wild rice mix (already cooked according to directions, including seasoning mix), other rice (already prepared), soups, cheese and mushrooms.
Mix well. Spoon into shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until done.
Very rich.
Makes a good dish for potluck supper or a side dish for large gathering.

title: new orleans praline chews
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except pecan halves.
Mix just until a soft dough forms.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten each with greased bottom of a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Place 3 pecan halves on each cookie.
Bake about 8 minutes.
Cookie will flatten and be chewy crisp.
Cool 1 or 2 minutes before removing from sheet.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: catalina chicken(low-fat)
directions: Place chicken in small baking pan and cover with salad dressing and basil.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cooked thoroughly.
Serves 1.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Note:
One 3 stack box grahams equals enough crushed crackers for double recipe!
One box confectioners sugar (sifted) equals 4 cups.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika and pepper in a large bowl.
Add chicken; coat well. Allow to marinate in sour cream mixture in refrigerator overnight, covered.

title: hamburger and rice
directions: Brown meat and onions and drain.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and then let simmer for 30 minutes. Top with strips of Cheddar cheese and let melt before serving.

title: yeast bread
directions: Place yeast in very warm water; stir and let stand until foaming.
Add yeast mixture to remaining ingredients.
Work with hands to make a soft dough.
Knead from 3 to 5 minutes, adding a little more flour if needed.
Place in a large, covered bowl.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Make out 30 rolls. Let rise.
Bake at 350°.
Brush with melted butter.
Use or freeze.

title: crusty fried oysters
directions: Combine egg and water.
Dip oysters in egg mixture and roll each in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot oil at 375° for about 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning to brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well and serve on lettuce.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Prepare dressing as directed on package. Saute onion and celery in margarine. Combine with chicken, soups and milk. Grease a 9x13 pan. Pour chicken mixture in pan and arrange dressing on top. Cover with foil or lid and bake at 350 for 1 hour. Remove foil for last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: butterscotch apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Combine butterscotch chips, sugar, flour, and cinnamon in small bowl, sprinkle over apples. Bake for 20 minutes, remove from oven.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Good dip for all fresh vegetables.

title: one dish chicken bake
directions: I use a roasting chicken from deli.

title: mary's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend in butter, flour, vanilla, salt, sugar and syrup.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Gently pour syrup mixture over nuts and bake at 300° for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese and Doritos.
Simmer all other ingredients until slightly thickened (about 30 minutes).
Put one layer sauce mix, one layer cheese and one layer Doritos.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Put in oven and heat until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: mashed potatoes au gratin
directions: Add fat, seasoning and eggs to hot, riced potatoes.

Add baking powder (to make potatoes light). Beat until light and mound in a baking dish. Cover with grated cheese, then cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 400° about 10 minutes, or until the crumbs are golden brown.

title: noodle and corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender in boiling water.
Drain and rinse. In large bowl, mix beef, soup, milk, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup of cheese together.
Pour in 4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle on rest of cheese and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes
a large batch.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat together the first 5 ingredients; set aside.
In another bowl, sift together the next 5 ingredients.
Add to this the water, vinegar, vanilla and cooking oil.
Beat until well blended. Fill paper lined muffin tins 1/3 to 1/2 full with chocolate batter.
Top with 1 heaping teaspoonful cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle top with granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili pork chops
directions: Score fat on chops and arrange in 3-quart casserole so "tails" are in center.
Place onion and green pepper slices on top of chops.
Pour chili sauce over top.
Cover.
Microwave at Medium (5) 34 to 38 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Lay Tater Tots in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sauce mix over potatoes.
Add ground beef on top.
Pour soup and water over ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Can add Cheddar cheese on top and heat until melted.

title: southern belle salad
directions: Drain cherries and bring 3/4 cup of juice to a boil. Add to gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Stir in Coca-Cola and lemon juice. Chill until gelatin mounds slightly. Cut cream cheese into very small pieces. Fold into gelatin. Add cherries and nuts to mixture. Spoon into 7 individual molds. Chill until firm.

title: banana berry cooler
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high for 30 seconds or until smooth.
An option would be to add 1/2 cup ice and blend well.
Makes 2 eight ounce servings.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in pecans. Combine remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine pie filling, pineapple, condensed milk, marshmallows and pecans in a bowl.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill until serving time.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add gradually to creamed mixture.
Drop by spoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes until brownish.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook the egg noodles according to the package instructions. In a saucepan combine the soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add the noodles and the chicken. Heat through over a low heat, stirring often. Garnish with parsley if desired. Serves 4.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until soft and smooth. Add flour, salt and vanilla; mix well. Add pecans, mix well and drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet. Cook at 350° for about 15 minutes, not too brown. While warm, roll in confectioners sugar twice.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix all together and form into patties.
Spray skillet with Pam.
Fry patties until brown on each side.
Makes 18 patties about 3-inches in diameter.
Low calorie when using tuna packed in water.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until thick and cool.
Arrange a layer of graham crackers, then a layer of pudding. Top with crushed graham crackers.

title: souffle sandwich
directions: Place 8 slices cubed bread (remove crusts - optional) in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bread with cheese.
Cover cheese with meat.
Add mushrooms over meat.
Cover with 8 slices cubed bread.

title: easy vegetable lo mein
directions: Mix chicken broth, soy sauce and cornstarch until smooth. Heat oil in wok or large saucepan.
Add mushrooms, celery and red pepper.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Stir in bean sprouts, scallions, snow peas and cornstarch mixture. Cook until sauce thickens and boils.
Add drained hot spaghetti; toss well.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients and press into bottom of long pan. Mix last four ingredients and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar until well blended.
Add salt.
Add 1 cup flour, beating well after each addition.
Knead 5 minutes with dough hook, or if you don't have a dough hook, lightly flour surface and knead 5 minutes.
Divide into 15 to 18 pieces.
Roll into balls, then make 14-inch rope.
Twist into pretzel shape. Brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Beat 1 egg lightly.
Add mayo, mustard, salt and plenty of pepper, whisking until smooth.
Add crab meat and parsley and toss lightly but thoroughly.
Shape into 6 cakes and carefully dip them in flour.
Beat second egg in a shallow bowl and dip crab cakes in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Cover with wax paper and refrigerate until well chilled and coating adheres, at least 30 minutes.
Heat butter or oil (or combination), in a heavy skillet and fry cakes until brown on each side.
Serve garnished with lemon wedges and accompany with coleslaw.
Makes 6 patties.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix together.
Chill and then form into eggs.
Coat with chocolate.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Bring water to boil and add next three ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for ten minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cheese, soup, and milk.
Stir until melted.
Then serve or cool and freeze.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Mix butter and Crisco until creamy.
Add salt and sugar slowly, then vanilla.
Beat on high until frosting.

title: heath candy
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Cook for 10 -12 minutes until medium brown over medium heat.
Butter cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts on cookie sheet.
Pour sugar and butter mixture on the cookie sheet.
When beginning to harden sprinkle top with milk chocolate chips.
Spread chocolate as it melts.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on top.
Break apart into irregular pieces when it cools.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs, pumpkin and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Spread evenly on a long cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and remove to cool for 5 minutes.
Invert on a dish towel and remove paper.
Roll long ways, towel and all.
Cool completely, approximately 15 minutes.
Unroll and fill with the following filling.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in blender.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into bite size balls or patties.
Brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush the graham crackers. Melt the butter. Mix the crackers, butter and powdered sugar together.
Line pan with 1/2 mixture. Cream the cream cheese, vanilla and sugar. Whip the Carnation milk until stiff.
Make jello and cool. Add creamed mixture and jello to whipped milk and mix thoroughly.
Pour in pan and top with remaining cracker crumbs.

title: meat loaf with piquant sauce
directions: Soak broken crackers in milk. Add meat, eggs, onion and seasoning; mix well and put into a loaf pan.

title: pauline's cheese ball
directions: Grate cheeses at room temperature.
Work all ingredients together except pecans.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: oatmeal no cook cookies
directions: Mix milk and peanut butter in pot and melt.
Add sugar and cocoa, after mixing it together.
Add vanilla extract.
Bring to a boil 1 or 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add oats all at once. Take off stove.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased plate.
Cut when cooled a little.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil or melted margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, sifted with salt and soda.
Add vanilla, nuts and apples.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together.
Place in a casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine with 1 stack Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Sprinkle crackers over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crunchy munchy peanut butter bars
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Cook and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter. Carefully stir in cereal, tossing lightly to coat.
With buttered or spray coated spatula, press mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces; press lightly.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars; contains 70 calories and 2 g fat.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Heat skillet with oil or grease.
Coat chops with flour.
Put in skillet to brown.
Have casserole dish ready.
Put browned chops in casserole dish.
Mix soup with 1 can of water and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until chops are tender.

title: honey-mustard sauce
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended.
Great over ham or roast beef.
Makes a great salad dressing.

title: california barbecue sauce
directions: On medium heat, combine all the ingredients.
Bring to boil. Reduce to simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup and water into baking casserole dish.
Lay pork chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: kraut
directions: Chop
cabbage
in
blender.
Pour in colander to drain. Pack in
quart
jars
and
add
1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar to each full jar.
Fill with warm water and wipe off all excess cabbage.
Put
tops
on (not too tight) and place in a cool place. Check often and add warm water to fill jars again for about a month after filling.

title: quick potato salad
directions: Cut slightly cooled potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, onions, salad dressing and bacon pieces; toss gently.
Dust with paprika or black pepper.
Garnish with chives.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, salt and soda in a bowl. Cream together butter and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture after well blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: In large Dutch oven, saute in butter onion, celery, peppers, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper, paprika, seasoning and red pepper.
Add crawfish tails; cook until tail curls.
Add water and flour, then cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
