title: frankie and johnnie's
directions: Grease cornstick pans well and heat in 450° oven while preparing batter.
Measure corn meal into bowl and add milk, beaten egg, melted shortening and chopped onion.
Slice each frankfurter into 16 slices.
Pour batter into 12 corn stick pans 1/3 full. Place 5 slices frankfurters on top of each.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter yummies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook to boiling; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, marshmallows and vanilla.
Stir until well blended and marshmallows melt.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.
When firm, store in airtight container.

title: baked potato pudding
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Mix potatoes with all other ingredients and pour in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until the top is browned.

title: bisquick chicken casserole
directions: Bake or stew chicken, saving the broth.
Debone chicken and put in 13 x 9 inch pan.
Mix soup and 1 cup broth; pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick with butter until crumbly; add 1/4 cup broth and milk.
Pour Bisquick mixture over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts for pie crust.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, half of Dream Whip and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Spread over crust. Prepare lemon pudding with milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread remaining Dream Whip over top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Layer meat mixture and potatoes until all is used.
Pour
soup over the layers and top with cheese.
Bake uncovered on 350 degrees until potatoes are done.

title: dog bones(cookies for humans.)
directions: Blended oatmeal:
Measure and process in blender or processor to a fine powder.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add salt, baking powder and baking soda to flour and oats.
Stir in thoroughly.

title: angel delight
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with Cool Whip.
Work the Cool Whip down around the cake. Spread pie filling over Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until done, but firm. Drain and add seasoning. Refrigerate overnight. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain vegetables in colander; toss vegetables with Parmesan cheese in 3 quart dish.
Pour butter over veggies.
Combine tomato sauce and salt; pour over veggies.
Top with onion rings. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Wash berries and drain. Mix berries and sugar.
Place in crust.
Place 4 pats of butter on top and cover with top crust. Bake at 350°.
Be sure to slit top crust.

title: honey baked beans
directions: Cover beans with cold water; soak overnight.
Cook beans with water about one hour; drain and reserve liquid.
Place half of bacon and half the onion on bottom of casserole dish.
Add beans, bacon and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and 1 3/4 cups of reserved liquid.
Pour over beans.
Cover; bake at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake one hour or until beans are soft.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Put pineapple and jello (I prefer strawberry) in a pot and heat until jello is dissolved.
Cool until it is the consistency of mayonnaise.
Add pecans and buttermilk; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce or serve as a dessert.

title: nachos supreme
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add beans, onion, olives, chilies, taco sauce to taste and cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400° in a pizza pan.
Dip nachos and enjoy!

title: taco salad
directions: Shred the lettuce.
Slice small the green pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Drain the kidney beans. Smash the Doritos into tiny pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour bottle of dressing on right before serving.

title: pineapple coconut cream
directions: Mix together; bake at 350° approximately 40 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter together.
Spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix orange jello, hot water, and cranberry sauce with mixer or blender.
Add pineapple (drained), celery (diced), and chopped nuts.
Mix together and pour in 9 x 13 pan.
Refrigerate.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs well. Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt slowly to mixture.
Fold in remaining ingredients one at a time.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni and put into a buttered dish.
In a pot, on low, mix everything until melted and bubbling.
Pour mixture over macaroni; top with bread.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese, and powdered sugar. Beat until creamy, set aside. Mix milk and pudding, beat together until almost thick. Mix gently with creamed mixture and fold in Cool Whip. Layer cookies, pudding mix, cookies, pudding mix, and cookies in flower pot. Add plastic flowers, gummy worms and a plastic shovel to serve, or layer in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: swiss steak and vegetables
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Dredge with flour and brown in salad oil.
Season.
Cut up potatoes and carrots.
Put all but peas in large pan and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add frozen peas and cook until done.

title: rice pilaff
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add bouillon cubes and butter.
Let cubes soften then add rice.
Stir.
Remove from stovetop and place in oven.
Bake at 350° until water is absorbed (about 30 minutes).

title: cornmeal balls
directions: Cook neck bones in 1 gallon water until tender and falls off bones.
Remove meat from bones.
Add spices to meat and set aside in a separate bowl.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the spinach in one cup of water with 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Save water.
Cook and drain pasta shells.
Mix cheese with shells, lightly.
Add eggs; fold.
Add bread crumbs; fold.
Add oil, then add spinach and water and mix together.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over the top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat Dream Whip, milk and vanilla together.
Add 10x sugar and beat.
Beat cream cheese until smooth, then add the Dream Whip mixture a little at a time.

title: instant dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water until dissolved.
Add sugar, buttermilk and Crisco oil to yeast.
Add flour and knead a few times.
Roll out on floured board; cut with biscuit cutter.
Put small amount of butter or margarine on each roll and fold in half. Put in a greased pan.
Let rise for 2 hours in a warm place. Bake in a preheated oven at 425°, until brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crackers.
Line one side of graham crackers with icing.
Lay, face down, on pudding.
Frost tops of crackers. Refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into large pieces.
Combine milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add bread pieces.
Put into a baking dish and pour butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
(Done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.)

title: heath bits of brickle
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in the butter as for pie crust. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage strata
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay bread in dish.
Fry sausage (crumbled) until not quite done.
Pour off grease and spoon onto bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix mustard, milk, eggs, salt and pepper together and pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Spread on dough.
Roll and cut into slices.
Let raise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chinese fruit bowl
directions: Combine all the fruits.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or longer.

title: squash pie(family recipe from nova scotia)
directions: I cook ahead "buttercup" squash and put in freezer. (Can use canned, but not the same flavor.) Line plate with uncooked crust. Put squash, sugar and spices in electric beater.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add scalded milk and pour into uncooked crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for balance of time, approximately 45 minutes.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix and allow to stand several hours or overnight.
Serve in a hollowed out loaf of marble bread.
Chop up remaining bread and use for dipping.

title: gazpacho dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate for 2 hours; drain.
Serve with Fritos or taco chips.

title: spanish rice and hamburger
directions: Saute onions and pepper in fat until brown.
Add hamburger, salt, pepper and chili powder.
When meat is slightly brown, place alternate layers of rice and meat mixture in casserole.
Pour tomatoes over dish and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: bessie weir's yummy soup
directions: Cook all vegetables and rice with a small amount of water until done.
Then add the soup.
The water in the cooked vegetables plus the undiluted soup will make sufficient liquid. Very good for a cold winter's day!

title: aunt carrie's chocolate cake and chocolate icing
directions: Add soda to milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: black beans with vinaigrette(makes 4 servings)
directions: Drain beans and rinse well.
Put in a large saucepan with water and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Lower heat, cover and simmer until soft, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Drain beans, remove bay leaf and return beans to saucepan.

title: green apple and sugared walnut salad
directions: Rinse and pat dry mixed greens, Blue cheese and walnuts. Add vinaigrette. Toss to coat and serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls together to form crust in jelly roll pan.
Bake and let cool.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Stir well and allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch cubes and marinate for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable surprise
directions: Place prepared carrots in a stew pot.
Cook until almost done. Add peas and potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 3 tablespoons of good cooking butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until all ingredients are done and tender.

title: raspberry coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package for 2 (9-inch) round cake layers, adding 2/3 cup of the coconut to batter.
Mix jam and 1 cup coconut in small bowl. Spread between cake layers.
Frost top and sides of cake with frosting.
Press remaining coconut on top and sides of cake. Garnish as desired.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: green tomato chow chow
directions: Wash and quarter tomatoes to measure 2 quarts. Grind onion, pepper and tomatoes. Pour hot water over tomato mixture and drain off rapidly. Put in pot to cook and add seasonings. Add enough vinegar to make soupy. Cook 25 minutes, stirring often.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine in a large bowl:
Mix milk, sugar, Crisco, salt, and baking powder.
Mix well and flour, 2 cups at a time until all is added.
Mix well.
Leave in bowl and grease top with oil.
Cover with a wet towel and let it sit until it has risen to double in size.
Push down and let it rise again.
After the second rise, make out into rolls and let them rise again.
Bake in 350 degree oven until brown.
If you do not wish to bake all of the rolls, place in refrigerator, covered, with wet cloth until ready to cook again.
Keep cloth wet.

title: tupperware pie crust
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in large Tupperware mixing bowl; seal and burp.
Shake approximately 3 or 4 minutes, or until ingredients look like large peas.
Add the cold water; seal and burp again.
Shake until ball forms.
Roll out.
Never fails!! Makes 3 single 9-inch crusts.

title: mexican hot soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and heat as desired.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight. Bake in a shallow casserole at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix tomatoes with vegetables; add 1/2 cup water and sprinkle tablespoon sugar.
Cover with foil.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Combine the potatoes, ham and onion in alternate layers in a 2-quart covered casserole.
Pour the white sauce over all.
Cover and bake in a moderately hot oven of 400° for 1 hour.
Remove the cover and bake about 30 minutes longer or until the potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: lucky charm treats
directions: Chop candy coating into small pieces.
Heat candy coating in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Stir in cereal and peanuts until completely coated.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper lined cookie sheet. Refrigerate until set.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: stanfield's ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar; beat well, until light.
Add the condensed milk; mix well.
Puree the strawberries; add pureed strawberries to mixture and mix well.
Pour into ice cream churn. Add the heavy or whipping cream and the half and half.
If not up to fill line, add small amount of whole milk until fill line is reached.
Churn.

title: creamy spinach lasagna(a low fat dish)
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving:
Prepare lasagna noodles as package directs.
Meanwhile, in a 10 inch non-stick skillet over medium heat, cook onion, mushrooms and garlic 5 minutes; remove from heat, then stir in spinach, oregano, basil and pepper.
Set aside.
In a food processor, blend cottage cheese, egg whites, flour and 1 cup mozzarella cheese until smooth.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a 13 x 9 inch baking dish, arrange 3 noodles; top with half of spinach mixture, half of tomato sauce.
Arrange 3 more noodles; repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles; sprinkle with remaining mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven, let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spudnuts(doughnuts)
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let rise.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with doughnut cutter and fry.

title: o' henry candy bars
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Spread in a 9 x 11-inch buttered pan.
Let cool, but don't refrigerate.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over mixture.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip with Eagle Brand and put in icebox.
Let set one hour, then mix remaining ingredients.
Mix all together; put in icebox overnight.

title: jumbo cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour and yeast.
Heat the milk, granulated sugar, 1/4 cup margarine or butter and salt just until mixture is warm (120° to 130°) and the margarine is almost melted, stirring constantly.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture; add eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds.
Scrape sides of bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Using a spoon, stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can (dough will be soft).
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately soft dough (3 to 5 minutes total). Shape dough into a ball.

title: szechwan-style pork cutlets
directions: Pound pork sirloin cutlets to 1/8-inch thick.
Brown cutlets, half at a time, in oil with garlic in frying pan over medium heat; pour off drippings.
Combine sherry, soy sauce, brown sugar and red pepper; pour over cutlets.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 20 minutes or until cutlets are tender.
Combine water and cornstarch.
Add to pan and cook until thickened.
Serve over vermicelli or rice.

title: gourmet cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Good on shrimp, etc.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Crumble this topping over the sweet potato mixture and bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: north meets south chowder(cold weather favorite)
directions: Bring to boil and cook until tender the potatoes.
Drain water until 1-inch below potatoes.
In frying pan, add oil and salt pork and cook until tender.
Add all corn without liquid from kernel corn.
Add pork and onions.
Set aside 1/2 cup half and half; add rest to potatoes.
To half cup, add flour and cornstarch.
Stir until dissolved.
Add to potatoes; cover.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Serve with sprinkle of paprika.
Serve cornbread with, or for something different.
Put corn bread in bowl, then add chowder.

title: juna's fettucini
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt for about 5 minutes.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook over very low for only a few minutes.
Remove from heat and add drained noodles and cheese.
Mix together well and serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: marinated pork roast
directions: Bake roast in 325°
oven
for
minutes
per
pound, marinating every 15 minutes
with mixture of honey, brandy and ginger.
Roast will be easier to carve if you have butcher cut out the bone.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Prepare rice as label directs.
Refrigerate cooked rice until well chilled.
In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs and salt lightly.
In 12-inch skillet over high heat, put 3 tablespoons salad oil and cook until very hot.
Pour in egg mixture.
Cook, stirring quickly and constantly with spoon, until eggs are the size of peas and leave the side of the pan.
Reduce heat to low. Push eggs to one side of skillet.
In same skillet, gently stir rice and 2 tablespoons oil until rice is well coated with oil. Add bacon and soy sauce; gently stir to mix all ingredients in skillet.
Heat mixture thoroughly.
Sprinkle with chopped green onions.

title: overnight coffeecake
directions: Mix together then add:

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, then drain off oil.
Add all other ingredients and simmer, the longer the better.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms, careful not to break caps.
Chop stems and saute with butter and onion.
Add seasonings and bread crumbs.
Place mixture in inverted mushroom caps.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour milk in dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot as appetizer.

title: cheese-ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut cheese into enough 1/4-inch thick slices to line bottom and side of greased 3-quart casserole to within 1-inch of top.
Reserve remaining cheese.
Mix ham, rice, soup, tomatoes, onion, green pepper and salt; pour into casserole. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Shred remaining cheese; sprinkle over walnuts.
Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly, 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Place peach halves in 1-quart jar.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling.
Pour over peaches and cool.
Cover; refrigerate at least 8 hours.
This can be made the day before and left to refrigerate.

title: pineapple crunch coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with vegetable spray.
Mix 2/3 cup of dry cake mix with brown sugar, walnuts and butter until crumbly.
Reserve.
Beat eggs and egg whites with sour cream.
Mix in remaining cake mix.
Spread half of batter in baking dish.
Top with half of the pineapple and sprinkle with half of the brown sugar mixture.
Spoon and gently spread remaining batter over brown sugar mixture.
Top with remaining pineapple and sprinkle with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: jello delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add berries and juice. Pour into bowl you will be serving it in.
Refrigerate until set.

title: microwave lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and lemon peel in deep 1-quart bowl.
Blend in water and lemon juice.
Microwave at High (100%) until sauce is thickened and clear, 2 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, stirring after half of cooking time.
Stir in margarine and egg yolk.
Microwave at High (100%) until bubbly, 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: clam casserole
directions: Drain juice off of clams into a cup measuring cup and fill up with milk.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: chicken stir fry
directions: Cook and stir vegetables in 1 Tbsp oil in a medium skillet for 5 minutes. Add chicken and sauce, cover for 2 minutes. Spoon over cooked rice.

title: overnight egg casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and add Jell-O; stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Combine cake mix and add dry jello.
Add other ingredients, adding eggs one at a time.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: triple chocolate coffee brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine egg, brownie, cooking oil, coffee liqueur or coffee, coffee or water, milk chocolate pieces, white chocolate baking pieces, semi-sweet chocolate pieces and the nuts.
Stir just until combined.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 brownies.

title: hot rolls
directions: Pour hot water into a large bowl, then add salt, butter and honey.
Stir until the butter is melted.
Cool slightly.
Put yeast into 1 cup of warm water. Add it to the ingredients in the large bowl.
Work in the flour until the dough is firm enough to knead.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Put dough in greased bowl, cover it with a damp cloth and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch the dough, divide it and shape. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mincemeat
directions: Peel, seed and chop pears and apples.
Cook all for 15 minutes.
Pack into hot jars with lids.
Store as for jam or jelly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, bacon and onion.
Make into a ball.
Roll in parsley, if desired.

title: yam apple hash
directions: Place yams in a medium saucepan with 1 1/2 cups of water. Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 40 minutes until yams feel done.
Drain yams and rinse out pan.
Place apples in the pan with 3 tablespoons of water.
Cover and cook for 3 minutes until barely done.
Remove pan from heat and mash apples with a fork.
Mash yams, butter and lemon juice.
Add sugar and nutmeg.
Stir in apple mixture.
Mix well and serve.

title: pot roast
directions: In a 3-quart pan, fill with 2 quarts of water.
Trim fat off meat and cut into large pieces.
Add onions and Millers seasoning. Cook for 3 hours.
Remove meat.
Cut vegetables and add to broth; cook for 1/2 hour.
Add meat and cook for 15 minutes and serve.

title: recliner meal
directions: Sit in recliner, put T.V. control in your hand and yell to your wife "Is it ready yet?"

title: granny's olive spread
directions: Mix well and chill.
Good on crackers or celery.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil, or use celery salt. Cook rice until done.
Add tomatoes (after draining rice).
Add butter; simmer 2 to 3 minutes, long enough to melt butter.
Add oregano; set aside.
Put oil in casserole dish; heat.
Add meat that has been cut in bite size pieces.
Mix into rice.
Add 3/4 cup water.
Bake for 30 minutes, or microwave for 12 minutes.

title: cucumber crisp pickles
directions: Make a syrup of 5 pounds sugar to 4 pints of apple vinegar. Tie cinnamon, allspice, ground cloves and ginger in a bag.
Add to syrup.
Bring to a boil and cook to dissolve sugar.
Soak cucumbers in lime water about 10 to 12 hours (overnight).

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet.

title: delicious rhubarb dessert
directions: Put into 13 x 9-inch pan in order given in layers.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream or just serve as is.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend dry ingredients well and add milk and beaten egg yolks. Cook until thick and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: see's candy store fudge
directions: Beat eggs and powdered sugar together well in mixer.
Melt chocolate chips with butter in microwave or double boiler.
Blend the 2 mixtures together with a spoon.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: turkey or chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat everything but soup and meat until boiling.
Add soup and meat.
Mix with cooked spaghetti.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry sponge cake
directions: Grease and flour two 8 x 1 1/4-inch pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt onto a sheet of wax paper.
Heat milk and butter just until small bubbles appear around edge.
Do not boil.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs until foamy in a small bowl.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar while continuing to beat until thick and fluffy; beat in vanilla and cooled milk.
Fold flour mixture gently into eggs until well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 25 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly with fingertip.
Cool layers on wire racks 10 minutes.
Wash, hull and slice strawberries.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes to allow juice to form.
Place one layer on a serving plate.
Spread with 1/2 whipped cream and top with 1/2 strawberries.
Top with remaining cake layer and follow the same.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine ham, pork, eggs, milk and corn flake crumbs; mix well. Shape into 3/4-inch balls and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: brownie glaze
directions: Microwave in 1-quart glass bowl on High 1 1/2 minutes until melted, stirring twice.

title: pizza
directions: Put in a mixing bowl lukewarm water and yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat well.
Add 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour or bread flour.
Beat until smooth. Add about 1 1/2 cups flour using enough to make the dough just barely firm enough to handle.
Knead until smooth.
Divide in thirds.
Knead each piece into a ball.
Flatten, then pull and stretch gently to fit 9-inch layer cake tins, lightly greased. Press up around the edges to make a slight rim.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Brush lightly with olive oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, grated.
Cover with fresh tomatoes or drained, canned tomatoes, slivers of Mozzarella or other Italian cheese, chopped anchovies or meat and sprinkling of oregano or basil.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.
Makes three 9-inch pizzas.

title: kracker jacks
directions: Place popcorn and nuts in a greased jellyroll pan.
Melt butter and sugar with syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Stir until coated.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring often after 15 minutes.
Cool and break.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruity bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Combine cereal and milk in another bowl. Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in egg whites and oil.
Add to flour mixture; stir until just moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl thoroughly combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, cinnamon,
baking soda and salt. Add to

Cool in pan.
Frost as desired.
Makes about 15 servings.

title: barbecues
directions: Place meat in 3-quart casserole.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cook at 350° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Mash and serve on buns.

title: pineapple nut cookies(pineapple is good in cookies.)
directions: In a bowl, beat all ingredients together.
Heat pizella iron, and when ready, drop a large tablespoon of batter or 1/4 cup. Close iron and let pizellas cook for a few seconds.
Remove with a fork.
Once cooled, they can be stacked on top of each other in a container for storage.
(I have used an empty oatmeal can.)
They can also be wrapped in foil for safe keeping.

title: kapusta
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut well.
Add beef cubes to water; pour over kraut.
Cover and boil 20 minutes.
Fry bacon, reserving drippings.
Add onion and brown; add flour and brown.
When kraut is done, drain and reserve juice.
Add kraut juice to flour mixture, stirring constantly.
When smooth, add to kraut and mix thoroughly.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Cut ends off cucumbers, pack in a gallon jar.
Put in the salt, pickling spice and alum.
Fill with cold vinegar and let stand 16 days.
After 16 days, empty and wash cucumbers and slice, then pack back into the jar.
Add the sugar, let stand 24 hours. Refrigerate and eat.
Keep them in refrigerator at all times.

title: dill and sour cream dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand at least 1 hour.
Serve as a dip with potato chips.
Some add chopped cucumber and/or shrimp to this tasty and economical dip.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix together; put in greased pan lined with chips. Put crushed chips on top with a little cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend in the melted butter, flour, sugar, salt, vanilla and syrup.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Gently pour in syrup mixture.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes, reduce heat to (325°) and bake about 40 minutes longer.
Yields an 8-inch pie to serve 6.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Wash the chicken and pat dry.
Melt shortening and butter in baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, in the oven.

title: sausage cheese squares
directions: Unroll dough; place in ungreased 13x9x2 inch baking dish. Press onto bottom and 1/2 inch up side to form a crust.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs in a bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Carefully pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cut into small squares.
Yield 12 to 16.

title: chicken bride and groom
directions: Cook and debone chicken breast.
Layer in casserole dish. Saute onion and celery in butter; layer on top of chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream together and layer over all.
Add one cup chicken stock and top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Steam broccoli for 12 minutes.
Drain.
Mix bread mix and eggs; add all other ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased baking pan.
Cook at 400° until lightly browned.

title: fruit roll-ups
directions: Line cookie sheet with plastic wrap. Drain fruit well.
(Note: Frozen fruit may be used, thawed and drained.)
Put fruit in a processor.
Blend to a fine puree. Spread the puree on the plastic covered cookie sheet, leaving the edges untouched.

Place cookie sheet in oven at the lowest possible setting (approximately 150°). Leave in oven overnight or all day or until the fruit is dry. Roll up the fruit in the plastic wrap and cut in desired size.

title: morman bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in milk and oil; mix well.
Pour into gallon container with lid to fit loosely.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Flour board, roll out and cut like biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: orange gumdrop date bread
directions: Pour 1 cup
hot
water	over
dates.
Let
stand for 15 minutes.
Cream butter
and
sugars
in
bowl.
Add eggs.
Add orange juice.
Add	dates, gumdrops and orange rind; mix well. Add mixture of	flour, baking powder, soda and salt; mix well. Pour into 2 greased
9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in
pans for 3 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Put pecans and coconut in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt butter and cream cheese enough to mix in powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put into baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set (can be done day before).

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large mixing bowl, except raisins and nutmeats.
Mix at medium speed with electric mixer 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in raisins and nutmeats.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter surprise cookie
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients.
Blend dry ingredients into cream mixture.
Stir in chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Gently push M&M's in center.
Don't press deep.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: baked artichoke appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish lightly sprayed with Pam or Wesson light.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil and milk.
Mix until there is no lumps.
Pour into a well oiled big iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes until top is golden brown.
My children's favorite.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add ketchup and tomato sauce.
Heat. Put into casserole dish.
Cut cheese into strips; spread over mixture.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together until thick, then add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers and bananas.
Put pudding between each layer.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and then add to shredded cabbage.

title: party mix
directions: Mix Chex, Bugles, pretzels, nuts and peanuts in a large roasting pan.
Mix oil, sauces, margarine and salts together and blend.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir mixture every 20 minutes.
Add additional seasonings to taste.
Keeps well for several weeks in an airtight container.

title: pork roast with corn bread and oyster stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Make a deep slit in back of each chop or pork loin.
In large saucepan, melt butter; add onion, celery, garlic and fennel seeds.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender; stir in Tabasco sauce and salt.
Add stuffing mix, oysters and oyster liquid; toss to mix well.
Stuff cornbread mixture into slits in pork.
(Any leftover stuffing may be baked in covered baking dish during last 30 minutes of roasting).
Place meat in shallow roasting pan.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes per pound or until meat thermometer inserted into meat registers 170°.
Remove to heated serving platter.
Allow meat to stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: mock chicken loaf
directions: Mash noodles in chicken soup as fine as possible.
Use a blender if you have one.
Combine all ingredients and spoon into baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
It will be quite soft when it comes from oven, but firms as it cools.

title: candy apples
directions: Cook sugar, cream of tartar, lemon juice, cloves and water to 300°. Add food coloring. Dip apples.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add water and seasoning mix. Layer in order:
refried beans, meat, taco sauce and cheese.
Bake at 400° until bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips, sour cream and black olives.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel and cut pears, onions and bell peppers; grind in food chopper or blender.
Drain water or juice in a large saucepan.

title: springtime salad
directions: Separate cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets.
Peel stem for tender greens.
Combine with red onion and grated cheese.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise, salt and bacon and add to veggies.
Mix well. Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: chili cracker snack
directions: Mix Crisco oil, dill, garlic and Ranch salad dressing over Buckeye Soup N Chili Crackers.
Mix well and let set for at least 1 hour.
Great for snacks or used in soup or chili.

title: danish puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup all-purpose flour.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture mix.
Round into ball; divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into strip 12 x 3-inches.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix both sugars, margarine and egg in large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt (dough will be stiff).
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: fresh pineapple salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine pineapple, onion and mint;
mix well. Serves 6.

title: sheilah chicken
directions: Boil and bone 4 chicken breasts.
Line bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass dish with chicken.
In separate bowl mix together undiluted soup and sour cream.
Pour soup-sour cream mixture over the chicken and spread evenly.
Crush Ritz crackers finely and spread over all.
Dot the top with margarine.
Bake at 325° until heated through.

title: quick after-school cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: candy bar brownies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and butter in large bowl.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into sugar mixture.
Coarsely chop Snickers bars and fold into batter.
Spoon into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with finely chopped chocolate bars. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over coconut.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions on box and pour over nuts.

title: fluffy pudding frosting
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Stir whipped topping into pudding very gently with a rubber spatula until mixture is all the same color.
Spread on cake or cupcakes.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: hawaiian bread french toast
directions: Slice Hawaiian bread in 1-inch thick slices and then in half. Beat eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon together.
Dip bread in batter and fry in butter on both sides until done.
Serve with syrup.
Scrumptiously delicious.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Beat pudding, milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Butter 9 x 13-inch pan lightly.
Line bottom with graham crackers, then layer half of pudding, another layer of crackers, remainder of pudding, top layer crackers.
Warm icing in microwave 1 minute and pour on top.
Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and gelatin, then with dry cake mix.
Pour water over mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rolls for freezing
directions: In large electric mixer bowl, place the 1 tablespoon sugar, yeast and lukewarm water.
Let yeast dissolve.
Add all other ingredients, adding flour gradually, beating constantly on low speed.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Let dough rise until double in size.
Make out rolls in your favorite size.
Brush tops with butter.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
The next morning, place in Ziploc bag.
When ready to bake, take rolls out and let them double in size.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add graham crackers, then add other ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: succotash
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Combine.
Add seasoning, butter and milk.
Heat very slowly in saucepan.

title: cheerio bars
directions: Bring to a full boil, first 4 ingredients.
Then pour over last 3 ingredients and mix and press into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and chill.
Garnish with M&M pieces.
Double for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
